1
00:01:22,591 --> 00:01:24,317
凯丽女士 过会儿我能和您谈谈吗
Miss Kelly, might I talk to you later?

2
00:01:24,755 --> 00:01:25,889
只要你说的话
Not if what you're going to say

3
00:01:25,914 --> 00:01:28,678
不会给我带来什么麻烦
will cause trouble for me in some way or another.

4
00:01:36,831 --> 00:01:39,070
姑娘们 早高峰已经过去了
9:00 mass is over, girls.

5
00:01:45,365 --> 00:01:46,859
- 好了 - 谢谢
- Now. - Thank you.

6
00:01:46,884 --> 00:01:47,727
- 请稍等一下 - 您好
- One moment, please. - Excuse me.

7
00:01:47,752 --> 00:01:50,229
再给我来一些熏肉和奶酪
And some rashers and some cheese.

8
00:01:53,951 --> 00:01:56,372
布雷迪夫人 您今天想来点什么
Mrs Brady, what would you like this morning?

9
00:01:56,397 --> 00:01:58,664
- 请给我来半打熏肉 - 好的 没问题
- Half a dozen rashers, please. - Of course.

10
00:01:58,689 --> 00:02:00,464
艾丽斯现在就给您打包
Eilis will get that for you now.

11
00:02:00,593 --> 00:02:03,341
- 下一个该我了 - 你还是下一个
- I was next. - And you still are.

12
00:02:05,779 --> 00:02:07,888
- 你要什么 - 我需要一些鞋油
- Yes? - I need some shoe polish.

13
00:02:07,913 --> 00:02:12,173
鞋油 周日不供应鞋油 你不知道吗
Shoe polish? That's not really a Sunday item, now, is it?

14
00:02:12,198 --> 00:02:14,754
这些人都是来买晚餐或下午茶的材料
These people need things for their dinner or their tea.

15
00:02:14,779 --> 00:02:17,201
你怎么昨天就不记得呢
Why couldn't you have remembered yesterday?

16
00:02:17,441 --> 00:02:19,675
看样子你昨天就需要鞋油了吧
Because it looks like you needed it yesterday.

17
00:02:20,137 --> 00:02:21,305
不好意思
I'm sorry.

18
00:02:34,732 --> 00:02:35,751
凯丽女士
Miss Kelly...

19
00:02:36,130 --> 00:02:38,698
我记得呢 你想说什么就说吧
I hadn't forgotten. Spit it out, whatever it is.

20
00:02:40,431 --> 00:02:42,114
我要去美国了
I'm away to America.

21
00:02:45,338 --> 00:02:46,617
这是谁的主意
Whose idea was that?

22
00:02:47,016 --> 00:02:49,580
纽约的弗勒德神父帮我安排的
Father Flood in New York arranged it.

23
00:02:49,910 --> 00:02:52,975
罗斯以前总是和他打高尔夫 他资助了我
Rose used to play golf with him. He sponsored me.

24
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,836
还给我介绍了工作 并且帮我搞定了签证
And he found me a job and got me a visa.

25
00:02:54,861 --> 00:02:56,497
等你回来之后 就不用来上班了
Well, we won't be needing you back here.

26
00:02:56,522 --> 00:02:58,192
在走之前 我可以每个周日都来上班
I could work every Sunday till I go.

27
00:02:58,217 --> 00:02:59,601
不用了
No, thank you.

28
00:03:02,391 --> 00:03:04,929
- 你的姐姐真可怜 - 我的姐姐
- Your poor sister. - My sister?

29
00:03:05,013 --> 00:03:08,682
这个国家的母亲 总是被长大的子女抛弃
Well, mothers are always being left behind in this country.

30
00:03:08,809 --> 00:03:10,559
但是罗斯
But Rose,

31
00:03:10,791 --> 00:03:12,942
她这辈子就只能这样了 不是么
that's the end for her now, isn't it?

32
00:03:12,967 --> 00:03:16,148
她的余生都要留在这里照顾你母亲了
She'll be looking after your mother for the rest of her life.

33
00:03:31,073 --> 00:03:32,158
罗斯 我真该把你的事情
I wish I'd written to

34
00:03:32,159 --> 00:03:33,506
写信告诉弗勒德神父
Father Flood about you, Rose.

35
00:03:33,531 --> 00:03:35,783
我吗 我有工作
Me? I have a job.

36
00:03:36,326 --> 00:03:37,803
你每个周日 都得花好几个小时
You had a couple of hours on a Sunday

37
00:03:37,804 --> 00:03:39,461
为内特尔斯·凯丽打工
working for Nettles Kelly.

38
00:03:39,486 --> 00:03:40,661
你不应该叫她的全名
You shouldn't call her that.

39
00:03:40,686 --> 00:03:42,540
对于她这种怪脾气的老女人
I think it's quite a kind name.

40
00:03:42,919 --> 00:03:45,428
我这么叫她 已经够客气的了
Considering she's actually a terrible old witch.

41
00:03:45,512 --> 00:03:48,042
行了 我不想再谈论她了
Well, I don't want to talk about her any more.

42
00:03:48,067 --> 00:03:49,048
好吧
Good.

43
00:03:51,586 --> 00:03:52,575
我听说美国的夏天更热
They say it's hotter there

44
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:54,711
冬天更冷
in the summer and colder in the winter.

45
00:03:57,051 --> 00:03:59,190
天哪 她去那里应该穿什么呢
What in heaven's name will she do about clothes?

46
00:03:59,215 --> 00:04:00,276
妈妈 她自己会买的
She'll buy them, Mother.

47
00:04:00,301 --> 00:04:02,153
她才不会把钱浪费在买衣服上面
She doesn't want to be wasting her money on clothes.

48
00:04:02,178 --> 00:04:04,902
她别无选择 她要在那里待...
She won't have much choice. She'll be there for...

49
00:04:20,329 --> 00:04:23,034
- 南希 你可真美 - 谢谢夸奖
- You look beautiful, Nancy. - Thank you.

50
00:04:23,925 --> 00:04:26,644
你这么漂亮 让我对这个地方都失望了
You look so beautiful. It makes me despair of this place.

51
00:04:27,098 --> 00:04:28,029
为什么
Why?

52
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:30,634
你可是韦克斯福德郡最漂亮的女孩
Well, you're the prettiest girl in County Wexford.

53
00:04:30,659 --> 00:04:32,578
你能随心所欲地挑选男生
You should be able to choose any man you want

54
00:04:32,849 --> 00:04:33,964
但愿橄榄球俱乐部的
and we're hoping that George Sheridan

55
00:04:33,989 --> 00:04:36,116
乔治·谢立丹能看上你
from the rugby club looks your way.

56
00:04:36,141 --> 00:04:37,525
你觉得他会吗
Do you think he might?

57
00:04:37,772 --> 00:04:39,339
肯定会的
Of course he will.

58
00:04:39,608 --> 00:04:43,777
{\an9\fs20}美国知名演员

59
00:04:39,608 --> 00:04:41,518
南希 我知道你喜欢他
I know you like him, Nancy,

60
00:04:41,519 --> 00:04:43,777
但他可不是加里·库珀 对吧
but he's not Gary Cooper, is he?

61
00:04:44,146 --> 00:04:47,229
而且那些男生喜欢抹发油 穿西装
And those boys with their hair oil and their blazers.

62
00:04:47,254 --> 00:04:49,252
- 他的眼睛很好看 - 嗯
- He has beautiful eyes. - Mmm...

63
00:04:49,277 --> 00:04:50,332
而且他可是要继承
And he's going to come

64
00:04:50,333 --> 00:04:52,953
一家集市广场中很不错的商店
into a beautiful shop in the market square.

65
00:04:55,062 --> 00:04:57,136
你怎么没穿你的蓝裙子
Why didn't you wear your blue dress?

66
00:04:57,561 --> 00:05:00,085
你是想说 我为什么不好好打扮一下吗
Are you asking why I didn't make more of an effort?

67
00:05:01,115 --> 00:05:02,963
可能是因为我要走了
I suppose cos I'm going away.

68
00:05:03,173 --> 00:05:04,677
小心 快走
Mind, now.

69
00:05:06,138 --> 00:05:07,338
快来
Come on.

70
00:05:37,223 --> 00:05:38,916
他已经往这边看了两次了
He's looked over here twice already.

71
00:05:38,941 --> 00:05:40,066
才没有
He hasn't!

72
00:05:42,124 --> 00:05:44,522
- 他现在往这边走过来了 - 你骗人
- He's walking over here now. - He's not!

73
00:05:45,022 --> 00:05:48,127
我为什么要拿乔治·谢立丹的事情骗你
Why would I keep lying to you about what George Sheridan's doing?

74
00:05:52,013 --> 00:05:53,774
能请你跳支舞吗
Would you like to dance?

75
00:06:43,016 --> 00:06:44,690
这就是你全部的家当吗
Is that really everything you own?

76
00:06:45,456 --> 00:06:46,525
哦 艾丽斯
Oh, Eilis.

77
00:06:47,505 --> 00:06:49,284
我应该好好照顾你的
I should have looked after you better.

78
00:06:49,630 --> 00:06:52,333
这箱衣服基本上都是你给我买的
You've bought most of the clothes in this case.

79
00:06:53,707 --> 00:06:55,215
我都不能自己买衣服
That's one of the reasons I'm going,

80
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:56,312
这也是我想离开家的原因之一
cos I can't buy my own.

81
00:06:56,337 --> 00:06:57,133
如果真是那样
If it was just that,

82
00:06:57,134 --> 00:06:59,393
我宁愿把挣到的每一分钱都花在你身上
I'd spend every penny I had on you.

83
00:06:59,821 --> 00:07:01,066
我很愿意
Gladly.

84
00:07:02,108 --> 00:07:04,308
但是我没法给你一个未来
But I can't buy you a future.

85
00:07:04,684 --> 00:07:07,087
我没法给予你想要的生活
I can't buy you the kind of life you need.

86
00:07:07,372 --> 00:07:08,404
我明白
I know.

87
00:07:11,355 --> 00:07:13,135
总有一天你会去看我的吧
But you'll come see me there one day?

88
00:07:13,347 --> 00:07:14,345
当然了
Yes.

89
00:07:16,420 --> 00:07:18,700
你会好好照顾自己吧
And you'll look after yourself?

90
00:07:18,725 --> 00:07:20,476
你不用担心我
You don't have to worry about me.

91
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:22,751
我能回家看看的 对吧
And I'll come home to visit, won't I?

92
00:07:24,583 --> 00:07:26,745
因为我会受不了...
Cos I couldn't bear it if...

93
00:07:26,770 --> 00:07:28,817
你还没把鞋子收拾好呢
You haven't packed your shoes yet.

94
00:07:29,484 --> 00:07:31,179
它们可要占不少位置
They'll take up a bit of room.

95
00:07:39,111 --> 00:07:40,152
好了
There.

96
00:09:27,543 --> 00:09:28,672
抱歉
I'm sorry.

97
00:09:40,513 --> 00:09:41,729
下来
Off.

98
00:09:42,241 --> 00:09:44,586
一号 下铺 是我的位置
Number one, bottom bunk, that's mine.

99
00:09:44,611 --> 00:09:45,725
你是上铺
You're on the top.

100
00:09:53,496 --> 00:09:54,505
这鬼地方真是地狱
This is hell.

101
00:09:55,048 --> 00:09:57,552
- 再也不要坐船了 - 再也不去美国了
- Never again. - Never again to America?

102
00:09:57,577 --> 00:10:00,574
当初我就不该从美国回来
The mistake was coming home from America in the first place.

103
00:10:01,929 --> 00:10:04,348
只要能不让我待在这鬼船舱 做什么都可以
I'd do anything to get out of this horrible cabin.

104
00:10:04,978 --> 00:10:06,367
一起出去抽根烟吧
Let's go for a smoke.

105
00:10:06,392 --> 00:10:07,684
我不会抽烟
I don't.

106
00:10:08,671 --> 00:10:10,687
随你便 一会儿见
Suit yourself. I'll see you later.

107
00:10:11,112 --> 00:10:14,039
但愿我能找到一个头等舱的男士作伴
Unless I find a nice man in First to smoke with.

108
00:10:32,212 --> 00:10:33,947
幸好还有人不受天气预报影响
It's good to see that not everybody's

109
00:10:33,948 --> 00:10:36,037
愿意来吃晚餐
put off their dinner by the weather forecast.

110
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:38,708
据说今晚天气很糟糕
It's supposed to be a rough one tonight,

111
00:10:38,733 --> 00:10:40,499
所以现在没别的乘客来用餐了
so none of the other passengers are eating.

112
00:10:40,740 --> 00:10:44,179
大概也就喝一点汤 但不会吃炖羊肉
A few spoonfuls of soup maybe, but not the mutton stew.

113
00:10:56,358 --> 00:10:57,733
请开门
Please unlock it.

114
00:11:27,265 --> 00:11:28,953
走开
Go away!

115
00:11:42,765 --> 00:11:44,554
对不起 搞得到处都是臭味
I'm sorry about the smell.

116
00:11:44,977 --> 00:11:46,366
还把水桶搞脏
And the bucket.

117
00:11:46,597 --> 00:11:49,072
别担心 整艘船都一片狼藉
Don't worry. The whole boat stinks.

118
00:11:49,097 --> 00:11:50,520
包括头等舱
Even First Class.

119
00:11:50,925 --> 00:11:52,857
忘了说 我刚从头等舱被赶出来了
I've just been thrown out of there, by the way.

120
00:11:52,882 --> 00:11:54,883
洗手间整晚都锁着
The bathroom door was locked all night.

121
00:11:56,466 --> 00:11:57,761
那些贱人
Oh, those bastards.

122
00:12:27,158 --> 00:12:29,841
好了 虽然过意不去 但毕竟厕所归我们了
There. Won't be very comfortable, but at least it's ours.

123
00:12:31,152 --> 00:12:33,204
- 开门 - 滚开
- Open the door. - Fuck off.

124
00:12:33,229 --> 00:12:35,110
- 快开门 - 我说了 滚开
- Open the door right now. - Do you hear me? Fuck off.

125
00:12:35,135 --> 00:12:37,871
如果你昨晚能友善一些 我们也会以礼相待的
If you'd been nice last night, we would have played fair.

126
00:12:37,896 --> 00:12:39,702
- 现在你们没得用了 - 滚出洗手间
- Now you've got no toilet. - Get out of the bathroom.

127
00:12:39,727 --> 00:12:40,977
贱人
You bastards.

128
00:12:42,047 --> 00:12:43,433
去吧 你可以用了
Go on, you can use it.

129
00:12:43,458 --> 00:12:46,142
我去拿点水来 你现在只能喝水了
I'm going to get us some water. That's all you're allowed.

130
00:12:52,852 --> 00:12:54,556
你要在美国定居吗
Are you going to live in America?

131
00:12:55,349 --> 00:12:56,186
是的
Yes.

132
00:12:56,580 --> 00:12:58,021
证件和其他东西都准备好了吗
You have papers and everything?

133
00:12:58,239 --> 00:13:00,583
是的 工作也有了
Yes. And a job.

134
00:13:01,087 --> 00:13:02,686
你是怎么搞定的
How'd you manage to arrange all that?

135
00:13:02,866 --> 00:13:04,893
不是我弄的 有人替我办好了
I didn't. Someone did it for me.

136
00:13:04,918 --> 00:13:06,540
是我姐姐认识的神父
A priest my sister knows.

137
00:13:06,743 --> 00:13:08,536
那你对此感觉怎么样呢
And how do you feel about it?

138
00:13:13,590 --> 00:13:16,091
从爱尔兰寄的信要多久能到美国
How long do letters from Ireland take to arrive?

139
00:13:16,449 --> 00:13:18,619
我姐姐罗斯说她会尽快给我写信
My sister Rose said she'd write straightaway.

140
00:13:18,673 --> 00:13:20,597
第一次要花很长时间
They take a long time at first.

141
00:13:21,244 --> 00:13:22,630
之后就会很快了
And then no time at all.

142
00:13:23,533 --> 00:13:25,540
你在美国有亲人或者朋友吗
You have family in America? Friends?

143
00:13:25,885 --> 00:13:26,865
没有
No.

144
00:13:26,994 --> 00:13:28,593
你会很快就交到朋友的
You'll meet people easily enough.

145
00:13:28,857 --> 00:13:31,249
你要住在哪里 布鲁克林吗
Where are you gonna live? Brooklyn?

146
00:13:31,897 --> 00:13:34,201
- 你怎么知道的 - 随便猜的
- How'd you know that? - Lucky guess.

147
00:13:35,024 --> 00:13:36,128
有时候跟素不相识的人聊天
Try to remember that sometimes it's

148
00:13:36,129 --> 00:13:38,641
是一件很愉快的事情
nice to talk to people who don't know your auntie.

149
00:13:39,649 --> 00:13:40,649
就像我们这样吗
That's what it's like?

150
00:13:41,099 --> 00:13:42,516
没错
That's what it's like.

151
00:13:48,864 --> 00:13:50,574
我已经好几个小时不犯恶心了
I haven't been sick for hours.

152
00:13:50,808 --> 00:13:52,242
太好了
Nice, isn't it?

153
00:13:53,467 --> 00:13:54,494
我现在好饿
I'm very hungry.

154
00:13:54,684 --> 00:13:56,724
所以你才好几个小时不恶心
That's why you haven't been sick for hours.

155
00:13:57,388 --> 00:13:58,999
明天再吃东西吧
We'll eat tomorrow.

156
00:13:59,801 --> 00:14:01,330
或者后天
Or the day after.

157
00:14:07,019 --> 00:14:10,260
亲爱的 我得把你改造一下
Oh, dear. We're gonna have to do something with you.

158
00:14:10,683 --> 00:14:12,257
不然你这样入境的话
They'll put you in quarantine or something

159
00:14:12,282 --> 00:14:14,459
他们会把你隔离的
if you try and enter the country looking like that.

160
00:14:15,747 --> 00:14:18,185
不能太花哨 不能看起来太招摇
Nothing fancy. You mustn't look like a tart.

161
00:14:18,858 --> 00:14:22,353
其实太招摇也没问题
Oh, well, looking like a tart isn't going to be a problem.

162
00:14:24,417 --> 00:14:25,923
这件看起来还不错
This doesn't look too bad.

163
00:14:26,139 --> 00:14:27,741
我姐姐给我买的
My sister gave me that.

164
00:14:30,630 --> 00:14:33,582
搭配上这件
Wear it with this

165
00:14:33,607 --> 00:14:35,024
和这件
and...

166
00:14:36,879 --> 00:14:38,121
还有这件
...this.

167
00:14:42,455 --> 00:14:44,606
将行李准备好 接受检查
Have your bags ready for inspection.

168
00:14:44,631 --> 00:14:46,588
别表现得一脸天真
Don't look too innocent, though.

169
00:14:47,819 --> 00:14:50,133
给你擦点口红 涂点睫毛膏
I'll put some rouge and mascara on you.

170
00:14:51,763 --> 00:14:53,553
再画个眼线也行
Perhaps a little eye liner.

171
00:15:05,622 --> 00:15:09,040
请站在线后面 下一位 谢谢
Step out of the line, please. Thank you. Next, please. Thank you.

172
00:15:09,946 --> 00:15:11,988
请往这边走 站在线后面
Step over this way, please. Get out of the line.

173
00:15:12,115 --> 00:15:13,740
下一位 请出示护照
Next. Passport, please.

174
00:15:13,825 --> 00:15:15,438
挺胸抬头
Stand up straight.

175
00:15:15,925 --> 00:15:17,371
擦亮鞋子
Polish your shoes.

176
00:15:17,680 --> 00:15:19,830
无论如何都不要咳嗽
And don't cough, whatever you do.

177
00:15:20,056 --> 00:15:21,723
往这边走
Over this way.

