347
00:26:11,215 --> 00:26:12,683
淑女些 别笑了
Ladies, please.

348
00:26:14,467 --> 00:26:15,968
艾丽斯 弗勒德神父让我问问你
Eilis, Father Flood told me

349
00:26:15,993 --> 00:26:17,236
圣诞节有什么计划
about your Christmas plans.

350
00:26:17,539 --> 00:26:18,757
你不会是要去给那些
Oh, you're not serving lunch

351
00:26:18,782 --> 00:26:20,531
无家可归的老家伙们送午餐吧
to the old fellas who've nowhere to go, are you?

352
00:26:20,821 --> 00:26:22,658
他每年都问我们去不去 我们都推了
He asks us every year. We always say no.

353
00:26:22,743 --> 00:26:25,112
艾丽斯 你可真是个好人 他们的味道很恶心
Eilis, you're a saint. They smell awful.

354
00:26:25,299 --> 00:26:26,326
希拉知道他们闻起来什么味道
Sheila knows how they smell

355
00:26:26,351 --> 00:26:27,872
因为她就在那堆人里面物色丈夫的
because that's where she goes husband hunting.

356
00:26:31,043 --> 00:26:32,937
艾丽斯 你做的这件事很棒
It's a marvellous thing you're doing, Eilis.

357
00:26:32,962 --> 00:26:34,420
这才是信徒该做的
A Christian thing.

358
00:26:34,646 --> 00:26:36,301
希望有更多人能像你一样
I wish there were more like you.

359
00:26:40,050 --> 00:26:41,484
请进
In you come.

360
00:26:42,544 --> 00:26:43,596
大概会来多少人
How many are we expecting?

361
00:26:43,722 --> 00:26:46,124
去年来了一百人 今年可能更多
We had a hundred last year. There may be more this.

362
00:26:46,314 --> 00:26:49,060
- 他们都是爱尔兰人吗 - 都是
- Are they all Irish? - All Irish.

363
00:26:50,216 --> 00:26:51,726
他们为什么不回家乡呢
Why don't they go home?

364
00:26:52,881 --> 00:26:54,031
如果像你这样
If there's nothing there for

365
00:26:54,056 --> 00:26:55,233
聪明又年轻的姑娘在那都无处傍身
clever young girls such as yourself,

366
00:26:55,359 --> 00:26:57,693
对于像他们这样的就更不容易了
there's gonna be even less for men like these.

367
00:26:57,902 --> 00:27:00,485
他们中有些人已经来了五十年了
Some of them have been here 50 years.

368
00:27:00,792 --> 00:27:02,198
与家乡完全断了音讯
They've lost touch with everyone.

369
00:27:02,282 --> 00:27:03,508
很好 谢谢你
Lovely. Thank you.

370
00:27:04,076 --> 00:27:05,785
- 圣诞快乐 - 谢谢
- Merry Christmas. - Thank you.

371
00:27:06,193 --> 00:27:09,246
是他们曾修桥开渠
These are the men who built the tunnels,

372
00:27:09,330 --> 00:27:11,219
铺路营建
the bridges, the highways.

373
00:27:11,797 --> 00:27:14,133
可现在天知道他们靠什么活着
God alone knows what they live on now.

374
00:27:29,418 --> 00:27:30,658
总之...
Anyway...

375
00:27:35,498 --> 00:27:37,650
我不想打断大家
I don't want to interrupt proceedings,

376
00:27:37,796 --> 00:27:41,314
但我相信大家都想向今天
but I'm sure you'd all like to show your appreciation

377
00:27:41,339 --> 00:27:43,656
为我们辛勤服务的女士们表示感谢
to all the ladies here for their hard day's work.

378
00:27:43,816 --> 00:27:45,169
另外感谢
And by way of a thank you,

379
00:27:45,194 --> 00:27:47,535
今天来了一位伟大的演唱家
we have a great singer in the room with us today.

380
00:27:48,008 --> 00:27:49,479
弗兰基
Frankie.

381
00:29:17,542 --> 00:29:19,085
小心
Mind yourself, there.

382
00:29:19,542 --> 00:29:45,158
{\an9\fs20}《Casadh An Tsúgáin》

383
00:29:55,080 --> 00:29:55,912
你想来客厅
Would you like to come

384
00:29:55,913 --> 00:29:57,845
喝一杯吗
into the front room for a glass of something?

385
00:29:58,083 --> 00:29:59,447
你应得的
You've earned it.

386
00:30:01,376 --> 00:30:02,980
你撑下来了
You survived.

387
00:30:04,975 --> 00:30:06,712
没那么糟糕
It wasn't so bad.

388
00:30:09,094 --> 00:30:11,137
- 圣诞快乐 - 干杯
- Happy Christmas. - Cheers.

389
00:30:16,564 --> 00:30:18,686
麦克亚当小姐要搬走了
Now, Miss McAdam is leaving us.

390
00:30:18,785 --> 00:30:20,955
她要去和在曼哈顿的姐姐一起住
She's going to live with her sister in Manhattan.

391
00:30:21,242 --> 00:30:23,626
她的房间是这栋房子里最好的
She has the best room in the house,

392
00:30:23,721 --> 00:30:24,653
地下室那间
the basement,

393
00:30:25,183 --> 00:30:27,820
有个单独的大门
and it has its own entrance.

394
00:30:27,946 --> 00:30:29,822
我只想让
Now, I can only let

395
00:30:29,948 --> 00:30:33,451
某类特定的女孩住在那
a certain kind of girl stay there.

396
00:30:27,946 --> 00:30:33,451
{\an9\fs20}此类型的建筑地下半层内部与房子相通但单独开门 故房东不易监管

397
00:30:33,952 --> 00:30:35,411
当然 我说的不是长相
Oh, and I'm not talking about looks here.

398
00:30:35,707 --> 00:30:38,080
虽然我得承认 在我考虑谁是最佳人选时
Although I will admit, God did give Miss McAdam an advantage

399
00:30:38,165 --> 00:30:40,458
上帝给了麦克亚当小姐一张安全的脸
when I had to think about who I could trust to live down there.

400
00:30:40,584 --> 00:30:42,460
其实你很漂亮 艾丽斯
No, no, you're a pretty girl, Eilis,

401
00:30:42,893 --> 00:30:44,628
关键在于你很懂事
but you're sensible.

402
00:30:45,261 --> 00:30:47,548
所以 那间房间归你了
So, you're having the room and that's that.

403
00:30:47,981 --> 00:30:49,543
其他人会介意吗
Will the other girls not mind?

404
00:30:49,718 --> 00:30:51,093
我猜会的
Oh, I expect so.

405
00:30:51,368 --> 00:30:53,088
有什么事是她们不介意的吗
What don't they mind?

406
00:30:58,760 --> 00:30:59,560
姑娘们 你们会带德洛莉丝去
Girls, you'll take Dolores to

407
00:30:59,561 --> 00:31:01,728
周六晚上的舞会 对吧
the dance with you on Saturday night, won't you?

408
00:31:01,753 --> 00:31:02,732
有舞会吗
There's a dance?

409
00:31:02,757 --> 00:31:04,002
在教区大厅
At the parish hall.

410
00:31:04,027 --> 00:31:06,919
不提供酒水 但是没酒你也一样能玩得开心
There'll be no alcohol, but you can have fun without it.

411
00:31:07,442 --> 00:31:10,696
帕蒂和我这周就不去了
Um... Patty and I aren't going this week.

412
00:31:11,800 --> 00:31:13,743
我们改为看电影了
We're going to see a movie instead.

413
00:31:14,066 --> 00:31:16,160
我相信德洛莉丝也很乐意去看电影的
Well, I'm sure Dolores would enjoy a movie just as well.

414
00:31:16,286 --> 00:31:17,745
我非常乐意
I would, very much.

415
00:31:17,829 --> 00:31:20,831
纽约的电影可比卡文多多了
There are so many more movies here in New York than in Cavan.

416
00:31:17,829 --> 00:31:20,831
{\an9\fs20}爱尔兰一城镇 为卡文郡郡治

417
00:31:20,957 --> 00:31:22,622
多新鲜哪
Yes, surprising, isn't it?

418
00:31:22,647 --> 00:31:24,278
你难道以为卡文的电影会更多吗
You'd think it'd be the other way round.

419
00:31:27,672 --> 00:31:30,373
没问题 我们当然欢迎你来 德洛莉丝
Of course, you would be welcome to join us, Dolores.

420
00:31:30,724 --> 00:31:32,676
只要你不介意当电灯泡的话
So long as you don't mind being a gooseberry.

421
00:31:32,928 --> 00:31:34,528
所以你俩在过去的几天里
So you both miraculously found

422
00:31:34,529 --> 00:31:37,108
都奇迹般地找到了男朋友吗
boyfriends over the last couple of days, did you?

423
00:31:38,012 --> 00:31:39,156
我希望你们这次
Well, I hope you have more

424
00:31:39,157 --> 00:31:41,227
能比前几次运气好点
luck with these than you did with the last few.

425
00:31:41,860 --> 00:31:44,234
- 艾丽斯 你去吗 - 我去 基欧夫人
- Will you be going, Eilis? - Yes, Mrs Kehoe.

426
00:31:44,364 --> 00:31:47,272
- 那你可以带德洛莉丝去 - 好的
- Well, you can take Dolores, then. - Of course.

427
00:32:09,172 --> 00:32:11,590
天哪 这都没什么人
God. There's nobody here.

428
00:32:12,956 --> 00:32:16,137
连人都没有 我们怎么找小伙子
How are we supposed to get a fella if there's nobody here?

429
00:32:16,221 --> 00:32:18,597
我想大多数人九点之后才会来
I expect most people will come after 9:00.

430
00:32:18,723 --> 00:32:20,850
人 还是小伙子
People or fellas?

431
00:32:21,990 --> 00:32:24,061
有人就会有小伙子
Some of the people will be fellas.

432
00:32:25,222 --> 00:32:26,991
我是来找男人的
I'd love to meet a fella.

433
00:32:29,662 --> 00:32:32,361
他们来了 这两个骗子
They came. The liars.

434
00:32:32,550 --> 00:32:34,742
真是一对贱人
What a pair of bitches.

435
00:32:35,640 --> 00:32:37,616
那些老妇人就是这么叫她们的
That's what the old woman called them.

436
00:32:37,894 --> 00:32:39,910
她说她们都是贱人
She said they were all bitches.

437
00:32:41,649 --> 00:32:43,094
你除外
Apart from you.

438
00:32:53,466 --> 00:32:55,176
嗨
Well, hello.

439
00:32:55,543 --> 00:32:57,501
嗨 很高兴看到你们
Hello. It's good to see you.

440
00:32:57,526 --> 00:32:58,902
看得出来
I can see why.

441
00:33:00,511 --> 00:33:02,429
跟我们来
Come with us.

442
00:33:16,329 --> 00:33:19,013
好了 这样好多了
There. That's better.

443
00:33:19,038 --> 00:33:21,660
这样你就不像刚给牛挤完奶了
Now you don't look like you came in from milking the cows.

444
00:33:21,987 --> 00:33:24,288
- 我看起来像那样吗 - 有点
- Is that what I looked like? - Just a bit.

445
00:33:25,099 --> 00:33:26,912
可爱的 干净的奶牛
Nice, clean cows.

446
00:33:27,294 --> 00:33:29,668
一 二 三
One, two, three.

447
00:33:29,794 --> 00:33:31,670
二 二 三
Two, two, three.

448
00:33:34,042 --> 00:33:35,174
跳得不错
Not bad.

449
00:33:35,300 --> 00:33:36,957
二...
Two...

450
00:33:45,977 --> 00:33:47,311
我们不如待会儿再跳吧
Maybe we can have a dance later.

451
00:33:47,765 --> 00:33:48,744
你说什么
I'm sorry?

452
00:33:48,769 --> 00:33:51,315
- 回头再跳 - 好的
- A dance, later. - Oh. Sure.

453
00:33:52,192 --> 00:33:54,181
能请你跳支舞吗
Would you like to dance?

454
00:34:06,331 --> 00:34:07,803
你是和那个
Are you here with that guy,

455
00:34:07,804 --> 00:34:09,875
教你跳舞的人一起来的吗
the one who was teaching you to dance?

456
00:34:10,001 --> 00:34:12,836
- 不是 - 那能请你跳支舞吗
- No. - So would you dance with me?

457
00:34:13,338 --> 00:34:14,922
我不确定我学会了
I'm not sure he taught me anything.

458
00:34:15,260 --> 00:34:16,257
无所谓
Doesn't matter.

459
00:34:16,341 --> 00:34:18,509
诀窍就是你看起来会就行
Secret is to look as though you know what you're doing.

460
00:34:19,682 --> 00:34:21,725
要是几年前有人这么告诉我就好了
I wish someone had told me that years ago.

461
00:34:23,733 --> 00:34:25,282
来吧
Come on.

462
00:34:57,507 --> 00:34:59,216
你住哪里
Where do you live?

463
00:35:00,815 --> 00:35:02,928
- 克林顿街 - 是吗
- Clinton Street. - Yeah?

464
00:35:04,159 --> 00:35:05,910
在我回家的路上
That's on my way home.

465
00:35:07,183 --> 00:35:09,018
我能送你回家吗
Can I walk you?

466
00:35:09,894 --> 00:35:12,813
可以 但我得告诉你 我同意的原因
I'm going to say yes and then I'm going to tell you why.

467
00:35:12,897 --> 00:35:14,732
以免我会错意
So I don't get the wrong idea?

468
00:35:14,858 --> 00:35:16,465
算是吧
I suppose so.

469
00:35:17,068 --> 00:35:21,196
看到那个穿白衬衫 独个坐在那里的姑娘了吗
Is there a girl in a white shirt sitting on her own over there?

470
00:35:25,744 --> 00:35:28,245
- 你不会认识她吧 - 没错
- You don't know her? - I do.

471
00:35:29,456 --> 00:35:32,249
她和我寄宿在同一件公寓 她很烦人
She lives in my boarding house and she's awful.

472
00:35:32,666 --> 00:35:34,835
如果我和你一起走了 我相信她能理解的
If I leave with you, I'm sure she'd understand.

473
00:35:34,919 --> 00:35:37,737
- 所以你这是救了我 - 我懂了
- You'd be rescuing me. - I get it.

474
00:35:59,110 --> 00:36:00,611
我不是爱尔兰人
I'm not Irish.

475
00:36:01,899 --> 00:36:03,553
你没有爱尔兰口音
You don't sound Irish.

476
00:36:04,785 --> 00:36:06,575
我得说明白
I need to make this clear.

477
00:36:06,659 --> 00:36:09,075
我一点爱尔兰血统都没有
No part of me is Irish.

478
00:36:09,329 --> 00:36:12,915
我父母不是 我祖父母不是 都不是
I don't have Irish parents or grandparents or anything.

479
00:36:13,261 --> 00:36:16,001
我是意大利人 反正我父母是
I'm Italian. Well, my parents are, anyway.

480
00:36:16,341 --> 00:36:18,128
那你为什么要来爱尔兰人的舞会呢
So what were you doing at an Irish dance?

481
00:36:18,429 --> 00:36:20,214
意大利人没有舞会吗
Don't the Italians have dances?

482
00:36:20,436 --> 00:36:22,633
有 但我不会想带你去参加的
Yeah, and I wouldn't wanna take you to one.

483
00:36:22,876 --> 00:36:24,843
整晚大家都特别意大利人
They behave like Italians all night.

484
00:36:24,969 --> 00:36:27,304
- 那是什么意思 - 你懂的
- What does that mean? - Oh, you know.

485
00:36:27,870 --> 00:36:29,074
我不太懂
No.

486
00:36:29,811 --> 00:36:30,933
鼓掌
Hands.

487
00:36:31,199 --> 00:36:32,267
总是鼓掌吗
Too many of them?

488
00:36:32,352 --> 00:36:33,612
我猜作为姑娘
I guess it could seem that way

489
00:36:33,613 --> 00:36:36,531
你应该会有这种感觉 听着...
if you was a girl. Listen...

490
00:36:39,805 --> 00:36:41,693
我想把话讲清楚
I want everything out in the open.

491
00:36:41,820 --> 00:36:44,930
我去爱尔兰舞会...
I came to the Irish dance...

492
00:36:46,402 --> 00:36:48,784
因为我特别喜欢爱尔兰姑娘
because I really like Irish girls.

493
00:36:49,714 --> 00:36:51,578
而我是唯一一个肯同你跳舞的吗
And I was the only one who would dance with you?

494
00:36:51,906 --> 00:36:53,038
不是 才不是...
Oh, no, it wasn't...

495
00:36:53,164 --> 00:36:55,791
所以你和很多人跳过吗
Oh, so you danced with loads of others?

496
00:37:04,843 --> 00:37:06,635
我到了
This is me.

497
00:37:09,180 --> 00:37:11,223
我下周能来接你吗
Can I take you next week,

498
00:37:11,349 --> 00:37:13,517
我们可以先去吃个晚饭
maybe get something to eat first?

499
00:37:15,353 --> 00:37:17,187
好的
That'd be nice.

500
00:37:18,801 --> 00:37:20,149
晚安
Good night.

501
00:37:39,286 --> 00:37:40,330
那么...
So...

502
00:37:42,729 --> 00:37:45,215
你不上班时都做些什么
What do you do when you're not working?

503
00:37:46,426 --> 00:37:48,760
我上夜校
Well, there's school.

504
00:37:49,142 --> 00:37:51,763
你知道的 布鲁克林学院
Just, you know, Brooklyn College.

505
00:37:52,007 --> 00:37:53,557
我在学记账
I'm studying book-keeping.

506
00:37:53,683 --> 00:37:55,392
你想当簿记员
You wanna be a book-keeper?

507
00:37:55,843 --> 00:37:58,193
以后我想做会计
Well, I want to be an accountant one day,

508
00:37:58,194 --> 00:37:59,938
不过没错 得先从簿记员开始
but, yes, book-keeping first.

509
00:38:02,567 --> 00:38:04,288
那些东西难吗
Is that difficult?

510
00:38:04,783 --> 00:38:07,760
我说得太多了 跟我说说修水管吧
I'm talking too much. Tell me about plumbing.

511
00:38:07,785 --> 00:38:09,573
你对修水管了解得够多了
You know enough about plumbing already.

512
00:38:09,699 --> 00:38:11,253
我什么都不了解啊
I don't know anything.

513
00:38:12,258 --> 00:38:16,097
你懂得水龙头漏水 马桶堵了
You know that taps drip and that toilets get blocked

514
00:38:16,122 --> 00:38:17,944
知道这些就够了
and that's all you need to know.

515
00:38:17,969 --> 00:38:20,385
我对记账可一无所知
I mean, I don't know anything about book-keeping.

516
00:38:24,422 --> 00:38:26,215
它包含很多东西
Well, there's a lot to it.

517
00:38:26,557 --> 00:38:29,426
全是数学 不过并不复杂
There's all the maths, of course, but that's not so complicated.

518
00:38:29,552 --> 00:38:32,054
只有复式记账法需要花些时间来适应
The double-entry system, that takes a while to get used to.

519
00:38:29,552 --> 00:38:32,054
{\an9\fs20}现代商业及其他金融交易的标准系统 即每一笔交易至少记录在两个不同的账户中 即借方和贷方 而且借贷总额相等

520
00:38:32,138 --> 00:38:35,685
而且我们还要学公司法 这部分很难
And we study company law too and that terrifies me.

521
00:38:35,710 --> 00:38:37,434
我们要阅读一篇三十年代
So we had to read about an insurance company

522
00:38:37,560 --> 00:38:39,436
破产保险公司的材料
that went bankrupt in the 1930s

523
00:38:39,562 --> 00:38:41,638
掌握其中所有相关的法律问题
and all the legal issues that went along with that.

524
00:38:41,824 --> 00:38:44,149
她打高尔夫 而且打得特别好
She plays golf and she's really good at it

525
00:38:44,275 --> 00:38:45,859
