- it'd break my heart. - Mine too.

698
00:47:23,744 --> 00:47:26,396
她没笑 托尼 看来为时已晚
She's not laughing, Tony. Think it's too late.

699
00:47:26,464 --> 00:47:27,965
她是个洋基队球迷
She's a Yanks fan.

700
00:47:28,340 --> 00:47:31,842
你在说什么 你怎么了
What are you talking about? What's wrong with you?

701
00:47:32,467 --> 00:47:34,137
她是个洋基队球迷
She's a Yanks fan.

702
00:47:55,853 --> 00:47:57,202
我爱你
I love you.

703
00:48:00,730 --> 00:48:01,859
我...
I...

704
00:48:04,156 --> 00:48:07,659
晚上谢谢你 我很开心
Thank you for the evening. It was lovely.

705
00:48:30,294 --> 00:48:31,623
哦 对不起
Oh! Sorry.

706
00:48:34,198 --> 00:48:35,865
我用完了
I'd finished.

707
00:48:43,822 --> 00:48:45,625
希拉 我能问你一些事吗
Sheila, can I ask you something?

708
00:48:47,788 --> 00:48:49,250
你为什么没有结婚
Why aren't you married?

709
00:48:53,094 --> 00:48:55,760
因为我的丈夫有外遇 离开了我
Because my husband met somebody else and left me.

710
00:48:56,328 --> 00:48:59,077
非常抱歉
Oh... I'm sorry.

711
00:49:00,695 --> 00:49:03,768
你会再结婚吗
And, well, would you get married again?

712
00:49:03,853 --> 00:49:05,776
- 有人向你求婚了吗 - 没有
- Has somebody asked you? - No.

713
00:49:07,600 --> 00:49:08,467
大概没有
Not really.

714
00:49:08,962 --> 00:49:10,495
我不会追问"大概"是什么意思
I won't ask what that means.

715
00:49:12,073 --> 00:49:13,508
我会再婚吗
Would I get married again?

716
00:49:13,676 --> 00:49:15,182
不 我想在寄宿公寓的厕所外
No, I wanna be waiting

717
00:49:15,207 --> 00:49:17,571
永远等下去
outside the bathroom of my boarding house forever.

718
00:49:18,181 --> 00:49:19,448
我当然想结了
Of course I do.

719
00:49:19,858 --> 00:49:22,620
所以我才每周都去那个恶心的舞会
That's why I go to that wretched dance every week.

720
00:49:22,989 --> 00:49:25,331
当某个脾气不好 头发乱糟糟的男人
I want to be waiting outside my own bathroom

721
00:49:26,357 --> 00:49:30,026
在厕所里读报纸时
while some bad-tempered fella with hair growing out of his ears

722
00:49:30,294 --> 00:49:32,422
我想在自己的厕所外面等
reads the newspaper on the toilet.

723
00:49:33,349 --> 00:49:36,407
然后我希望 还能回到这儿 和你聊天
Then I'll wish I was back here talking to you.

724
00:50:17,843 --> 00:50:19,302
艾丽斯
Eilis!

725
00:50:20,305 --> 00:50:21,638
对不起
I'm sorry.

726
00:50:22,209 --> 00:50:23,579
我没想到你会来
I didn't think you were coming.

727
00:50:23,604 --> 00:50:25,826
我知道 我猜你也没想到
Yeah, I know. I thought you were gonna think that.

728
00:50:25,851 --> 00:50:28,228
因此无论如何我都要来这儿
That's why I wanted to be here no matter what.

729
00:50:28,664 --> 00:50:30,272
- 我要和你说一些事 - 你能...
- I need to say something to you. - Can you...

730
00:50:30,273 --> 00:50:31,223
在到我们到基欧夫人的家之前
Can we just talk about

731
00:50:31,248 --> 00:50:33,399
我们能说点别的吗
something else until we get to Mrs Kehoe's?

732
00:50:33,484 --> 00:50:35,151
- 不是... - 求你了
- It's not... - Please.

733
00:50:38,018 --> 00:50:39,197
所以...
So...

734
00:50:40,830 --> 00:50:42,460
我早就该到了
Ten minutes before I'm supposed

735
00:50:42,485 --> 00:50:44,670
但一个老女人的天花板里漏了污水
to meet you and I'm standing ankle-deep in sewage

736
00:50:44,695 --> 00:50:46,621
我站在及膝的污水里耽搁了十分钟
that's pouring through this old lady's ceiling.

737
00:50:46,961 --> 00:50:47,997
是的
Yeah.

738
00:50:48,252 --> 00:50:50,774
即使你想邀请我喝杯咖啡
Even if you're thinking of inviting me in for a coffee,

739
00:50:50,799 --> 00:50:52,710
为了不熏到你 我只能拒绝
I'd have to say no for your sake.

740
00:50:52,967 --> 00:50:54,754
那你怎么在十分钟里修好的
So how did you fix it in 10 minutes?

741
00:50:54,996 --> 00:50:57,637
没修好 我花了整整十分钟给那位女士解释
I didn't. I spent the whole 10 minutes explaining to the lady

742
00:50:57,662 --> 00:50:59,795
我必须去别的地方 而且我会回来的
I had to be somewhere and I'd be back,

743
00:50:59,895 --> 00:51:01,336
但她还是不想让我走
and she don't wanna let me go.

744
00:51:01,496 --> 00:51:04,013
所以污水还在从天花板往下喷吗
So the sewage is still pouring through the ceiling?

745
00:51:04,610 --> 00:51:05,348
嗯...
Oh...

746
00:51:05,432 --> 00:51:06,944
六英寸和一英尺
Well, what's the difference

747
00:51:06,945 --> 00:51:09,185
有什么区别呢
between six inches of sewage and a foot?

748
00:51:10,792 --> 00:51:12,772
能让我说想说的话了吗
Will you let me say what I want to say?

749
00:51:13,986 --> 00:51:15,900
我觉得你不会介意吧
I don't think you'll mind.

750
00:51:16,026 --> 00:51:17,110
说吧
Ok.

751
00:51:20,446 --> 00:51:24,019
你还记得 你带我回家吃完晚餐后
You remember that after I had dinner at your house,

752
00:51:24,044 --> 00:51:25,635
你告诉我 你爱我吗
you told me you loved me?

753
00:51:28,090 --> 00:51:30,373
当时我不知道该怎么回应
Well, I didn't really know what to say.

754
00:51:32,284 --> 00:51:34,116
但现在我知道了
But I know what to say now.

755
00:51:36,371 --> 00:51:40,726
我已经考虑过了 我喜欢你
I have thought about you, and I like you.

756
00:51:41,848 --> 00:51:43,729
我喜欢和你在一起
And I like being with you.

757
00:51:45,398 --> 00:51:46,720
还有...
And...

758
00:51:48,597 --> 00:51:51,436
也许我和你感觉一样
maybe I feel the same way.

759
00:51:53,666 --> 00:51:56,015
所以下次你再说你爱我时
So the next time you tell me you love me,

760
00:51:56,514 --> 00:51:58,262
如果有下一次...
if there is a next time...

761
00:52:00,351 --> 00:52:02,155
我会说 我也爱你
I'll say I love you too.

762
00:52:05,692 --> 00:52:07,271
你说真的吗
Are you serious?

763
00:52:08,309 --> 00:52:09,407
真的
Yes.

764
00:52:11,915 --> 00:52:13,333
天啊
Holy shit.

765
00:52:13,604 --> 00:52:14,860
原谅我说粗话
Excuse my language,

766
00:52:14,885 --> 00:52:18,458
但我还以为 你要和我说些别的
but I thought we were having a different kind of talk.

767
00:52:19,757 --> 00:52:21,299
我现在可以回家了吗
Can I go home now?

768
00:52:21,561 --> 00:52:22,550
你爱我吗
You love me?

769
00:52:22,808 --> 00:52:25,498
爱你 但别问我除此之外的东西
Yes, but don't ask me anything else,

770
00:52:25,523 --> 00:52:27,764
也别谈论我们的孩子是道奇队球迷
and don't talk about our kids being Dodgers fans.

771
00:52:27,789 --> 00:52:29,766
怎么 你想要喜欢洋基队的孩子吗
What, you want kids who like the Yankees?

772
00:52:29,850 --> 00:52:32,301
托尼 求你了 别逼我
Tony, please, don't push me.

773
00:52:32,326 --> 00:52:33,831
好吧 对不起
All right. I'm sorry.

774
00:52:36,152 --> 00:52:39,984
"亲爱的艾丽斯 谢谢你的尼龙袜
"Dear Eilis. Thank you so much for the nylons.

775
00:52:40,110 --> 00:52:44,113
巴托奇的包装纸让它们看起来那么迷人
The Bartocci wrapping paper makes them look so glamorous.

776
00:52:45,130 --> 00:52:46,806
和这里相比
It seems everything is so exciting

777
00:52:46,831 --> 00:52:48,997
那里一切看起来都那么兴奋和新奇
and new compared to here.

778
00:52:49,961 --> 00:52:52,911
我都等不及 让你来向我展示一切
I can't wait for you to show it all to me one day.

779
00:52:56,726 --> 00:52:58,069
艾丽斯
Oh, Eilis,

780
00:52:59,027 --> 00:53:02,131
记住 即使我不在你身边 我也和你在一起"
you know I'm by your side, even when I'm not."

781
00:53:24,092 --> 00:53:25,527
好吧...
Well...

782
00:53:28,436 --> 00:53:30,827
我只能这么说 你棒极了
You're marvellous, that's all I have to say.

783
00:53:31,489 --> 00:53:34,746
看起来 你不仅通过了那些考试
It looks to me as if you didn't just pass those exams.

784
00:53:35,611 --> 00:53:37,774
而且考得很好
No. You flew through them.

785
00:53:37,885 --> 00:53:39,062
我都记不起上一次
I can't remember the last

786
00:53:39,087 --> 00:53:40,909
有人带来好消息 是什么时候了
time anyone came in here with good news.

787
00:53:41,178 --> 00:53:42,497
我攒了一些钱
I've saved some money.

788
00:53:42,758 --> 00:53:43,960
我可以支付下一年的学费
I'll be able to pay for next

789
00:53:43,985 --> 00:53:46,031
还能还给你去年的学费
year's tuition and pay you back for last year.

790
00:53:46,056 --> 00:53:47,654
学费是一个教区居民付的
One of my parishioners paid.

791
00:53:47,836 --> 00:53:51,266
他想要做一些好事 而我不会告诉你为什么
He needed to do something for mankind and I won't tell you why.

792
00:53:51,405 --> 00:53:52,792
因为他还没有走出困境
He's not out of the woods yet either,

793
00:53:52,817 --> 00:53:54,225
所以他还可以勉强交明年的学费
so he can cough up for next year, too.

794
00:53:54,514 --> 00:53:56,136
我想知道 他遇到什么困难了
I'd love to know what sort of woods he's in.

795
00:53:56,161 --> 00:53:59,121
当然 你会知道的 但我不会告诉你
Yes, I'm sure you would, but you won't hear it from me.

796
00:54:00,397 --> 00:54:03,019
有资格证书和男朋友了 艾丽斯
Qualifications and a boyfriend, Eilis.

797
00:54:03,442 --> 00:54:04,071
你不再是去年冬天
You're not the miserable

798
00:54:04,096 --> 00:54:06,259
那个可怜想家的女孩了
young girl who wanted to go home last winter.

799
00:54:06,572 --> 00:54:08,422
感觉像多年以前的事了
It seems like years ago.

800
00:54:09,145 --> 00:54:12,910
我想这是第一次
Now, I think this is the first time

801
00:54:13,226 --> 00:54:18,234
在我这里住的女孩通过考试
any girl of mine has ever passed an exam while living here.

802
00:54:21,683 --> 00:54:23,875
- 你告诉托尼了吗 艾丽斯 - 当然
- Have you told Tony yet, Eilis? - Of course.

803
00:54:23,962 --> 00:54:25,341
他打算带你出去庆祝吗
And is he taking you out to celebrate?

804
00:54:25,516 --> 00:54:27,675
我们打算周末去科尼岛
We're going to Coney Island at the weekend.

805
00:54:27,951 --> 00:54:30,157
- 天啊 - 什么意思
- Oh, boy. - What does that mean?

806
00:54:30,339 --> 00:54:31,525
你有泳衣吗
Do you have a bathing costume?

807
00:54:31,812 --> 00:54:33,848
- 没有 我打算去... - 你有墨镜吗
- No, I was going to... - Do you have sunglasses?

808
00:54:34,077 --> 00:54:35,913
- 没有 - 你需要墨镜
- No. - You need sunglasses.

809
00:54:35,986 --> 00:54:37,507
我听说 如果你去海滩上不戴墨镜
I read that if you don't have them on the beach this year,

810
00:54:37,561 --> 00:54:39,061
人们会讨论你
people'll talk about you.

811
00:54:39,401 --> 00:54:41,942
那他们到底会说什么 希拉
And what exactly will they say, Sheila?

812
00:54:42,242 --> 00:54:43,774
这就是问题所在 基欧夫人
That's the thing, Mrs Kehoe.

813
00:54:44,013 --> 00:54:47,010
你永远不会知道 因为他们不会当面说
You'd never know cos they'd never say it to your face.

814
00:54:48,413 --> 00:54:52,143
上帝啊 但戴安娜说得对 艾丽斯
Oh, dear God. Diana's right, though, Eilis.

815
00:54:52,168 --> 00:54:54,076
你需要好好考虑你的泳衣
You need to think carefully about your costume.

816
00:54:54,161 --> 00:54:55,431
这是托尼最想看你穿的衣服
It's the most Tony will ever

817
00:54:55,432 --> 00:54:57,747
而你也不想让他失望
have seen of you and you don't want to put him off.

818
00:55:02,419 --> 00:55:03,753
你那个地方需要剃毛
You'll have to shave down there.

819
00:55:03,837 --> 00:55:05,129
我给你一个剃须刀就可以搞定了
I'll give you a razor that'll do the trick.

820
00:55:10,969 --> 00:55:12,428
目前看起来你没什么问题
You're all right there for the moment.

821
00:55:12,513 --> 00:55:14,805
大多数意大利男人都喜欢丰满的身材
And most Italian men appreciate a fuller figure.

822
00:55:15,766 --> 00:55:17,767
但夏天你要注意
But watch yourself over the summer.

823
00:55:19,436 --> 00:55:21,938
你的皮肤很白 黑色太暗了 我们试试绿色吧
Black's too dark for your pale skin. Let's see you in the green.

824
00:56:02,396 --> 00:56:03,454
你为什么不告诉我
Why didn't you tell me

825
00:56:03,455 --> 00:56:05,523
要把泳衣穿在衣服下面呢
to put my costume on underneath my clothes?

826
00:56:05,649 --> 00:56:07,358
我以为你知道
I thought you'd know.

827
00:56:09,903 --> 00:56:11,904
我好了
Right, I'm ready.

828
00:56:20,080 --> 00:56:22,039
- 托尼 - 怎么了
- Tony. - What?

829
00:56:23,041 --> 00:56:24,208
来
Come on.

830
00:56:25,544 --> 00:56:28,546
"亲爱的罗斯 谢谢你的信
"Dear Rose. Thank you for your letter.

831
00:56:28,672 --> 00:56:31,090
我很高兴听到你的高尔夫比赛
I was happy to hear about your golf tournament.

832
00:56:31,174 --> 00:56:33,426
你一定非常高兴吧
You must have been really pleased.

833
00:56:34,011 --> 00:56:37,555
我还是思念你和妈妈 每天都想你
I still miss you and Mother and think about you every day,

834
00:56:37,681 --> 00:56:39,055
我想我可以说
but I think I can say that

835
00:56:39,056 --> 00:56:41,434
这是来美国后第一次
for the first time since I've been in America

836
00:56:41,518 --> 00:56:43,227
我真的感到开心
I'm really happy.

837
00:56:44,187 --> 00:56:46,230
这归功于托尼
This has a lot to do with Tony.

838
00:56:46,356 --> 00:56:48,983
周末他带我去看布鲁克林道奇队
At the weekend he took me to see the Brooklyn Dodgers,

839
00:56:49,067 --> 00:56:51,444
这是他喜欢的棒球队
the baseball team he loves.

840
00:56:51,528 --> 00:56:53,696
他们输球了 他很生气
They lost, so he was annoyed.

841
00:56:53,780 --> 00:56:56,782
我也已经开始找一份白领工作了
But I've also started to look for office work too.

842
00:56:56,867 --> 00:57:00,786
这周我在布鲁克林的纺织厂有一个面试"
I had an interview this week at a textile firm here in Brooklyn."

843
00:57:00,871 --> 00:57:02,121
罗斯
Rose.

844
00:57:02,205 --> 00:57:05,458
"谁会想到一个家庭里有两个记簿员呢"
"Who'd have thought there would be two book-keepers in the family?"

845
00:57:05,542 --> 00:57:06,584
罗斯
Rose.

846
00:57:10,213 --> 00:57:13,424
"我很快就能回家看你和妈妈了"
"I'll soon be able to afford to come home and see you and Mammy."

847
00:57:16,803 --> 00:57:18,220
罗斯
Rose?

848
00:57:21,933 --> 00:57:22,975
罗斯
Rose.

849
00:57:23,226 --> 00:57:24,560
上帝啊
Oh, my God.

850
00:57:26,938 --> 00:57:29,732
罗斯 哦 罗斯
Rose! Oh, Rose!

851
00:57:47,334 --> 00:57:48,751
稍等
One moment.

852
00:58:09,940 --> 00:58:11,607
事发突然
It was sudden.

853
00:58:13,360 --> 00:58:16,612
我想也许她生病了 而且她知道自己病了
I think perhaps she was ill, and she knew she was ill,

854
00:58:16,822 --> 00:58:19,031
但她没有告诉任何人
and she didn't tell anybody.

855
00:58:23,995 --> 00:58:26,497
- 接下会来怎样 - 还能怎么样
- What'll happen? - What can happen?

856
00:58:28,709 --> 00:58:31,293
- 他们什么时候埋葬她 - 明天
- When will they bury her? - Tomorrow.

857
00:58:33,714 --> 00:58:36,132
- 可我不在啊 - 不用你在
- Without me? - Without you.

858
00:58:37,217 --> 00:58:39,343
你离得太远了 艾丽斯
You're too far away, Eilis.

859
00:58:44,307 --> 00:58:46,392
我为什么要来这里
Why did I ever come here?

860
00:58:47,144 --> 00:58:49,228
罗斯希望你有更好的生活
Rose wanted a better life for you.

861
00:58:49,521 --> 00:58:50,980
她喜欢你现在的生活状态
She loved how well you were doing.

862
00:58:51,148 --> 00:58:53,315
但我不能再见到她了
But I'll never see her again.

863
00:58:57,195 --> 00:58:59,113
我说的没错吧 神父
That's right, isn't it, Father?

864
00:58:59,197 --> 00:59:01,323
我再也见不到她了
I'll never see her again.

865
00:59:01,742 --> 00:59:04,160
你会与她相见的
You know that I think you will.

866
00:59:04,703 --> 00:59:05,875
在你余生的每一天
And that she'll be watching

867
00:59:05,876 --> 00:59:07,830
她都会注视着你
over you every day for the rest of your life.

868
00:59:35,942 --> 00:59:37,943
你好 妈妈
Hello. Mammy?

869
00:59:42,949 --> 00:59:44,200
我听不太清
I can't really hear you.

870
00:59:46,536 --> 00:59:48,704
雨迟迟没下
Well, the rain held off anyway.

871
00:59:50,791 --> 00:59:54,043
她高尔夫俱乐部的人都来了 一个也没少
And the whole of her golf club came, every single one of them.

872
00:59:54,878 --> 00:59:57,213
满屋都是人
We had a real houseful afterwards.

873
01:00:00,300 --> 01:00:01,884
还在吗
Are you still there?

874
01:00:02,886 --> 01:00:04,220
我在
Yes.

875
01:00:07,098 --> 01:00:09,391
艾丽斯 大伙都很爱她
People really loved her, Eilis.

876
01:00:10,393 --> 01:00:13,229
工作伙伴 邻居们 大家都喜欢她
Her friends from work, the neighbours, everybody.

877
01:00:16,066 --> 01:00:18,234
大伙都不知道怎么安慰我
Nobody knew what to say to me.

878
01:00:21,738 --> 01:00:24,114
你爸去世时 我跟自己说
When your daddy died, I said to myself

879
01:00:24,241 --> 01:00:26,575
我还有你们俩 不要太难过
that I shouldn't grieve too much because I had the two of you.

880
01:00:28,119 --> 01:00:29,370
你远去美国时
And then when you went to America,

881
01:00:29,454 --> 01:00:32,790
我也这样跟自己说 因为我还有你姐姐
I told myself the same thing because she was here with me.

882
01:00:33,166 --> 01:00:34,575
但现在大家都不在了
But everyone's gone,

883
01:00:34,576 --> 01:00:36,126
艾丽斯 只剩下我一个人
Eilis. I have nobody.

884
01:00:57,107 --> 01:00:59,024
托尼 我受不了了
I can't bear it, Tony.

885
01:01:04,114 --> 01:01:08,951
你是想回家吧
You wanna go home, I guess.

886
01:01:12,497 --> 01:01:15,457
要是我走了 你会怎么办
How would it be for you if I did go home?

887
01:01:15,625 --> 01:01:19,461
我每天都会不安
I'd be afraid every single day.

888
01:01:19,963 --> 01:01:22,464
怕我不回来
Afraid that I wouldn't come back?

889
01:01:22,883 --> 01:01:24,300
是的
Yeah.

890
01:01:24,885 --> 01:01:26,510
但家总归是家
But home is home.

891
01:01:32,475 --> 01:01:34,476
我不确定那还是不是我的家
I'm not sure I have a home any more.

892
01:01:40,650 --> 01:01:43,152
你明天不去上班了吧
You're not going to work tomorrow, are you?

893
01:01:43,904 --> 01:01:46,864
弥撒之后 我能带你出去玩吗
After the Mass, can I take you somewhere?

894
01:01:59,836 --> 01:02:01,253
就是这里了
This is it.

895
01:02:02,756 --> 01:02:05,716
可能的话 我们要在这建五座房子
We're gonna build five houses here if we can

896
01:02:05,842 --> 01:02:08,427
要给爸妈一套
and Mom and Dad, they're gonna have one

897
01:02:08,511 --> 01:02:11,597
因为妈妈总想要个带后院的房子
cos Ma always wanted a house with a backyard.

898
01:02:11,681 --> 01:02:13,432
三套卖了
We'll sell three.

899
01:02:14,225 --> 01:02:16,018
还剩一套
And the other one,

900
01:02:16,269 --> 01:02:18,604
我兄弟问我想不想要
my brothers, they asked me if I wanted it

901
01:02:18,688 --> 01:02:20,648
我说我想要
and I said that I did.

902
01:02:20,732 --> 01:02:24,051
我想说的是
So I guess what I'm saying is,

903
01:02:24,093 --> 01:02:25,778
你想住在长岛吗
you wanna live out here on Long Island?

904
01:02:26,529 --> 01:02:28,614
我知道现在说这些还早
I mean, I know it doesn't look like much right now,

905
01:02:28,698 --> 01:02:30,699
但这附近的地都卖完了
but all the land around here has been sold,

906
01:02:30,784 --> 01:02:32,618
所以我们不会没有邻居的
so we wouldn't be on our own,

907
01:02:32,702 --> 01:02:36,705
以后还会有电话线 电和其他的一切
and there'd be telephone cables and electricity, everything.

908
01:02:44,756 --> 01:02:47,049
我们要创建家公司
We're gonna set up a company.

909
01:02:47,717 --> 01:02:50,302
建筑公司 我们三个人
A building company, the three of us.

910
01:02:50,387 --> 01:02:52,162
我负责管道工程
And I'm gonna do the plumbing

911
01:02:52,413 --> 01:02:54,306
劳伦斯管木工活...
and Laurence'll do the carpentry and...

912
01:03:01,564 --> 01:03:03,649
别不说话啊
Don't go all quiet on me.

913
01:03:04,651 --> 01:03:06,777
至少告诉我你会考虑一下
At least tell me you'll think about it.

914
01:03:11,408 --> 01:03:13,742
这根本不用考虑
I don't need to think about it.

915
01:04:04,711 --> 01:04:06,712
我就去一个月
It's just for a month or so.

916
01:04:08,798 --> 01:04:10,507
这样会让她好受些
I know it'd make her feel a little better.

917
01:04:20,143 --> 01:04:22,561
走之前嫁给我好吗
Will you marry me before you leave?

918
01:04:26,149 --> 01:04:28,484
你不相信我会回来吗
You don't trust me to come back?

919
01:04:31,029 --> 01:04:32,571
嫁给我吧
Marry me.

920
01:04:34,240 --> 01:04:35,657
嫁给我吧
Marry me.

921
01:04:36,367 --> 01:04:38,452
不必告诉别人
We don't have to tell anybody.

922
01:04:38,536 --> 01:04:42,081
很快办个手续 不跟别人说
We just do it quickly, just keep it between us.

923
01:04:45,085 --> 01:04:47,169
你为什么想结婚
Why do you want to do it?

924
01:04:48,171 --> 01:04:51,090
如果不这样的话 我会疯掉的
Because if we don't, I'm gonna go crazy.

925
01:04:56,888 --> 01:04:59,348
我的承诺就没有用吗
Would a promise not be the same?

926
01:05:02,060 --> 01:05:05,562
要是你能许诺的话 那结婚也算不了什么
If you can promise, you can easily do this.

927
01:05:49,816 --> 01:05:53,152
这就是你住的地方
So this is it. This is where you live.

928
01:05:53,653 --> 01:05:56,196
是的 要是你弄出响声
Yes, and if you make one tiny noise,

929
01:05:56,281 --> 01:05:57,489
她会赶我走的
she'll evict me.

930
01:07:31,042 --> 01:07:33,252
现在你不用担心了
There's no point in worrying now.

931
01:07:35,672 --> 01:07:37,339
留在我身边
Stay with me.

932
01:08:07,745 --> 01:08:09,413
要玩吗
You wanna play?

933
01:08:09,539 --> 01:08:11,623
- 可以啊 - 好的 来吧
- Yeah, sure. - All right, here we go.

934
01:08:11,749 --> 01:08:13,875
球棒马上就好
One bat coming up, huh?

935
01:08:14,294 --> 01:08:16,962
我拿着这个 准备好了没 举棒
I'll take that. All right, you ready? Hands up.

936
01:08:17,088 --> 01:08:18,630
- 好 - 球来了
- Yeah. - All right.

937
01:08:18,715 --> 01:08:20,924
正好在第三垒线上
Boom. Oh! Right down the third base line.

938
01:08:21,050 --> 01:08:22,134
他是不是很烦人
Is he annoying you?

939
01:08:22,218 --> 01:08:24,219
- 我可被他烦到了 - 没有 没有
- Cos he was annoying me. - No, no, no, no.

940
01:08:24,345 --> 01:08:26,513
我有个弟弟和他一样大
I got a brother the exact same age.

941
01:08:26,597 --> 01:08:29,016
- 你是爱尔兰人 - 很明显吗
- Hey, are you Irish? - Is it so obvious?

942
01:08:29,100 --> 01:08:31,092
我要娶一个爱尔兰女孩
I'm just about to marry an Irish girl,

943
01:08:31,093 --> 01:08:32,561
所以我更注意这一点
so I guess I notice it more.

944
01:08:32,687 --> 01:08:34,062
布鲁克林有很多爱尔兰人
There are a lot of you in Brooklyn.

945
01:08:34,188 --> 01:08:36,732
感觉老家都没几个人了
Sometimes it seems as though there can't be anybody left at home.

946
01:08:36,858 --> 01:08:37,858
你爱人住在哪
Where's your girl from?

947
01:08:37,942 --> 01:08:39,609
威克斯福德郡的恩尼斯柯西
Enniscorthy in County Wexford.

948
01:08:39,736 --> 01:08:41,403
我妻子在那儿有亲戚
My wife has family there.

949
01:08:41,529 --> 01:08:43,530
艾丽斯 过来一下
Hey, Eilis. Come here a sec.

950
01:08:43,614 --> 01:08:47,117
安东尼·费欧雷洛和艾丽斯·莱西
Anthony Fiorello and Eilis Lacey.

951
01:08:47,243 --> 01:08:49,536
- 好运 - 谢谢
- Good luck. - Thank you.

952
01:08:49,620 --> 01:08:51,955
走吧 快过来 走吧
Come on, come over here. Come on.

953
01:09:00,465 --> 01:09:03,050
要跟孩子们说这些吗
Will we ever tell our children we did this?

954
01:09:04,469 --> 01:09:07,220
还是留到纪念日再说吧
Maybe we'll save it for some anniversary.

955
01:09:08,931 --> 01:09:11,099
不知道他们会怎么想
I wonder what they'll think of it.

956
01:09:36,834 --> 01:09:39,419
- 南希 - 你真美
- Nancy. - You look so glamorous.

957
01:09:39,670 --> 01:09:41,505
我跟你说了的
I told you so.

958
01:09:41,631 --> 01:09:42,964
罗斯的死 请节哀
I'm so sorry about Rose.

959
01:09:43,758 --> 01:09:45,008
谢谢
Thank you.

960
01:09:45,176 --> 01:09:46,635
你怎么样了
How are you?

961
01:09:48,304 --> 01:09:49,304
不会吧
No.

962
01:09:49,430 --> 01:09:51,681
我早知道了 但我想让南希自己告诉你
I knew, but I wanted to let Nancy tell you herself.

963
01:09:51,808 --> 01:09:53,725
你能参加我的婚礼我很开心
I'm so glad you can come to the wedding.

964
01:09:53,810 --> 01:09:54,976
我可以去吗
Can I?

965
01:09:55,103 --> 01:09:58,313
你母亲替你收下了邀请函
Your mother accepted the invitation on your behalf.

966
01:09:58,439 --> 01:10:00,649
- 什么时候 - 八月二十七号
- When is it? - The 27th of August.

967
01:10:00,817 --> 01:10:03,235
明晚陪我和乔治出去吧
Will you come out with George and me tomorrow night?

968
01:10:03,319 --> 01:10:04,945
安妮特也想见你
Annette wants to see you, too.

969
01:10:05,029 --> 01:10:07,406
你去吧 我回去给你把钥匙
Oh, I don't mind. I'll have to find you a key.

970
01:10:07,490 --> 01:10:08,949
我不想让你吵醒我
I don't want you getting me out of bed.

971
01:10:09,033 --> 01:10:12,077
我们想听你在纽约的事
We all want to hear what life in New York is like.

972
01:10:12,161 --> 01:10:14,329
我尽量别没话说就好
I'll try and think of something to say.

973
01:10:21,963 --> 01:10:24,673
我订了二十一号回纽约的票
I'm booked to go back to New York on the 21st.

974
01:10:25,550 --> 01:10:29,052
你可以再呆一周 参加你闺蜜的婚礼
Well, you can wait an extra week to see your best friend married.

975
01:11:06,048 --> 01:11:09,217
真不敢相信 我嫁给了个你不认识的人
I can't believe I'm married to someone you'll never know.

976
01:11:14,515 --> 01:11:16,516
但你会喜欢他的
But you'd like him.

977
01:11:17,393 --> 01:11:19,227
我感觉你会的
I know you would.

978
01:11:22,064 --> 01:11:23,773
他对我很好
He's sweet.

979
01:11:24,859 --> 01:11:26,401
为人风趣
And he's funny.

980
01:11:27,195 --> 01:11:30,071
他那双漂亮的眼睛...
And he's got these wonderful eyes that...

981
01:11:41,751 --> 01:11:44,419
事情不这样发展就好了
I wish everything were different.

982
01:12:04,106 --> 01:12:06,942
到库什的奥图尔夫人了
So, now, Mrs O'Toole from Cush.

983
01:12:07,068 --> 01:12:08,652
真的要这么做吗
Do we really have to do this?

984
01:12:08,778 --> 01:12:10,095
收到吊唁信
Getting a letter of condolence

985
01:12:10,096 --> 01:12:12,072
和收到生日礼物可不一样
isn't like getting a birthday present, is it?

986
01:12:12,156 --> 01:12:13,597
要是库什的奥图尔夫人
What if Mrs O'Toole from Cush

987
01:12:13,598 --> 01:12:15,784
回信感谢你怎么办
writes back to thank you for your thank you?

988
01:12:15,910 --> 01:12:16,993
那我就再谢谢她
Then I'll thank her.

989
01:12:17,119 --> 01:12:19,496
余生都在写这些信 你很开心吗
And you'd be happy to spend the rest of your life like that?

990
01:12:19,622 --> 01:12:21,273
反正我也闲得无聊
It's not as if I've anything else to do

991
01:12:21,857 --> 01:12:22,666
也没人和我聊天
or anybody else to talk to.

992
01:12:22,792 --> 01:12:25,752
还不如写信给库什的奥图尔夫人
It might as well be Mrs O'Toole from Cush.

993
01:12:26,963 --> 01:12:28,380
你想要我说什么
What do you want me to say?

994
01:12:30,466 --> 01:12:33,969
- 肯定是南希和安妮特 - 你去吧
- That'll be Nancy and Annette. - Off you go.

995
01:12:37,932 --> 01:12:39,474
玩得开心
Enjoy yourself.

996
01:12:56,284 --> 01:12:57,993
艾丽斯 这位是吉姆·法雷尔
Eilis, this is Jim Farrell.

997
01:12:59,287 --> 01:13:01,329
见到你我很高兴
It's a great pleasure to meet you.

998
01:13:05,059 --> 01:13:06,977
我们可以去康诺特酒店的酒吧
We could try the Connaught Hotel bar.

999
01:13:07,002 --> 01:13:09,165
在那里可能会有些橄榄球俱乐部的人
There may be a few of the fellas from the rugby club there.

1000
01:13:09,190 --> 01:13:10,334
可以
Ok.

1001
01:13:12,067 --> 01:13:12,845
你一定要和
Do you have to be with

1002
01:13:12,870 --> 01:13:15,384
橄榄球俱乐部的人在一起吗
other fellas from the rugby club all the time?

1003
01:13:15,845 --> 01:13:17,206
不是的
No.

1004
01:13:18,472 --> 01:13:21,318
但南希说我们不能和你说话
But Nancy told us we wouldn't be allowed to talk to you

1005
01:13:21,343 --> 01:13:22,999
因为你们姐妹俩要叙叙旧
cos you have too much to say to each other,

1006
01:13:23,024 --> 01:13:24,853
我们只是去找些伴
so we're just looking for company.

1007
01:13:25,709 --> 01:13:26,688
原来如此
Oh, well.

1008
01:13:26,894 --> 01:13:29,095
艾丽斯 你不喜欢打橄榄球的人吗
Do you not like the fellas from the rugby club, Eilis?

1009
01:13:29,152 --> 01:13:30,859
也不能这么说 乔治
I don't particularly, George.

1010
01:13:31,254 --> 01:13:32,658
我去美国的时候
When I first went to America,

1011
01:13:32,683 --> 01:13:36,047
想念恩尼斯柯西的一切 除了橄榄球
I missed every single thing about Enniscorthy except one.

1012
01:13:36,173 --> 01:13:37,532
我们无时无刻都在改变
We're not all the same.

1013
01:13:37,573 --> 01:13:39,073
可你看起来没怎么变啊
You all look the same.

1014
01:13:39,709 --> 01:13:41,995
西装 喜欢摸发油 都一样
It's the blazer and the hair oil.

1015
01:13:51,234 --> 01:13:52,213
南希
Nancy.

1016
01:13:54,893 --> 01:13:56,998
安妮特呢 还有他怎么来了
Where's Annette? And why has he come?

1017
01:13:57,503 --> 01:14:00,013
他人不错 别为难他
He's very nice, so don't be too hard on him.

1018
01:14:00,385 --> 01:14:01,540
这是那个跟凯瑟琳·卡西迪
Is this the same Jim Farrell

1019
01:14:01,565 --> 01:14:03,208
订婚了的吉姆·法雷尔吗
that was engaged to Cathleen Cassidy?

1020
01:14:03,321 --> 01:14:05,352
- 她人呢 - 他取消婚约了
- What happened to her? - He broke it off.

1021
01:14:05,377 --> 01:14:07,104
他觉得她对待感情不够认真
He didn't think she was serious about him.

1022
01:14:07,266 --> 01:14:10,065
他伤心了一阵子 但现在都忘了她
He was very upset for a while, but he's over her now.

1023
01:14:11,149 --> 01:14:13,809
南希 我会回美国的
Nancy, I'm... I'm going back.

1024
01:14:14,050 --> 01:14:17,059
在这里就开心地玩吧 好吗
But you can have a bit of fun while you're here, can't you?

1025
01:14:17,769 --> 01:14:19,407
我们走 乔治
Come on, George.

1026
01:14:22,857 --> 01:14:24,267
你母亲还好吧
How's your mother?

1027
01:14:25,247 --> 01:14:28,458
她... 很伤心
She's... Well, she's sad.

1028
01:14:29,081 --> 01:14:31,378
一夜之间 老了很多
She's got much older very quickly.

1029
01:14:32,416 --> 01:14:33,867
那种事确实让人很难过
It was a terrible thing.

1030
01:14:34,315 --> 01:14:35,632
我们都去了葬礼弥撒
We all went to the funeral Mass,

1031
01:14:35,850 --> 01:14:37,534
我们全家都去了
Mother and Father and myself.

1032
01:14:38,204 --> 01:14:39,719
这我倒不知道
I didn't know that.

1033
01:14:39,920 --> 01:14:41,721
我妈和你姐姐一起打高尔夫
My mother played golf with her, you know.

1034
01:14:41,952 --> 01:14:43,433
我妈很喜欢她
She was very fond of her.

1035
01:14:43,991 --> 01:14:45,100
真是...
It was...

1036
01:14:46,428 --> 01:14:47,363
这是从我记事起
It was the saddest thing

1037
01:14:47,388 --> 01:14:49,484
镇上发生过最痛心的事
to happen in the town that I can remember.

1038
01:14:51,167 --> 01:14:52,351
谢谢
Thank you.

1039
01:14:54,068 --> 01:14:55,717
快来 你们俩
Come on, you two.

1040
01:15:00,433 --> 01:15:02,158
摩天大楼呢
And what about the skyscrapers?

1041
01:15:02,421 --> 01:15:03,910
那是在曼哈顿
Ah, but that's Manhattan.

1042
01:15:03,994 --> 01:15:06,393
我工作和生活都在布鲁克林
I live in Brooklyn and I work in Brooklyn,

1043
01:15:06,418 --> 01:15:08,419
出门的话 也是在布鲁克林
and if I go out, I go out in Brooklyn.

1044
01:15:08,521 --> 01:15:10,473
摩天大楼都在河对面
All the skyscrapers are across the river.

1045
01:15:10,613 --> 01:15:12,575
你说起来好像也没多好
You don't make it sound very glamorous.

1046
01:15:12,784 --> 01:15:13,654
是不怎么样
It's not, really.

1047
01:15:13,787 --> 01:15:15,300
别这样说 你工作的百货商店
Not even, what do you call it,

1048
01:15:15,325 --> 01:15:16,698
叫什么来着
the department store where you work?

1049
01:15:16,723 --> 01:15:19,536
叫巴托奇 卖些招人喜欢小玩意
Oh, Bartocci's? Well, it sells lovely things.

1050
01:15:19,561 --> 01:15:22,470
很多我都买不起 况且我也不喜欢那份工作
But I can't afford many of them and I don't like the work, so...

1051
01:15:22,980 --> 01:15:24,305
那你喜欢做什么
What would you like to do?

1052
01:15:25,737 --> 01:15:27,225
我想做罗斯的工作
I want to do what Rose did.

1053
01:15:27,397 --> 01:15:30,070
我想在办公室里上班 跟数字打交道
I want to work in an office and deal with numbers.

1054
01:15:30,095 --> 01:15:31,521
那你可以去戴维斯那里看看
Well, you should call in at Davis's.

1055
01:15:31,905 --> 01:15:33,857
他们还没找到接替罗斯的人
They haven't managed to replace Rose, you know.

1056
01:15:33,983 --> 01:15:36,651
婚礼过后我就要回纽约了
I'll be going back to New York straight after the wedding.

1057
01:15:36,851 --> 01:15:39,342
那你可以顺便赚些小钱
But you might want to earn a little money in the meantime.

1058
01:15:39,855 --> 01:15:41,197
你去的话 他们会很高兴的
I'm sure they'd be glad to have you.

1059
01:15:41,542 --> 01:15:43,131
你就是想要她留下来
You just want her to stay.

1060
01:15:45,728 --> 01:15:47,152
这是为艾丽斯着想
I'm only thinking of Eilis.

1061
01:15:47,305 --> 01:15:50,162
听见了没 艾丽斯 他在为你着想
Do you hear that, Eilis? He's only thinking of you.

1062
01:15:58,279 --> 01:15:59,692
没错 没错
That's it, that's it.

1063
01:15:59,717 --> 01:16:02,023
记得吗 戈尔甘夫人都没察觉到
Remember, Mrs Grogan didn't notice a thing.

1064
01:16:07,016 --> 01:16:08,625
- 晚安 - 晚安
- Good night. - Good night.

1065
01:16:08,650 --> 01:16:09,726
再见
See you.

1066
01:16:28,725 --> 01:16:30,121
晚上过得怎样
How was your evening?

1067
01:16:30,802 --> 01:16:32,553
很开心 谢谢关心
It was very nice, thank you.

1068
01:16:32,866 --> 01:16:35,154
我看车里面那个是吉姆·法雷尔吗
Was that Jim Farrell I saw in the car with them?

1069
01:16:36,359 --> 01:16:37,378
是的
It was.

1070
01:16:37,505 --> 01:16:38,669
他父母要搬走了
His parents are moving, you know.

1071
01:16:38,670 --> 01:16:39,798
都要退休回乡下了
They're retiring to the country.

1072
01:16:39,882 --> 01:16:41,716
马上他就能独自住一栋大房子了
He'll be in that big house on his own.

1073
01:16:41,980 --> 01:16:42,952
是吗
Is that right?

1074
01:16:45,178 --> 01:16:46,913
他是个不错的小伙子
He's a catch for someone.

1075
01:16:49,214 --> 01:16:50,396
晚安 妈妈
Good night, Mammy.

1076
01:17:02,611 --> 01:17:03,357
你好 艾丽斯
Hello, Eilis.

1077
01:17:03,358 --> 01:17:04,572
你好啊 布伦南夫人
Hello, Mrs Brennan.

1078
01:17:05,032 --> 01:17:06,746
真漂亮
Quite the star.

1079
01:17:14,293 --> 01:17:16,292
- 你终于回来了 - 怎么了
- Thank goodness you're back. - What's the matter?

1080
01:17:16,418 --> 01:17:17,862
戴维斯的人刚来了
A lad from Davis's came round.

1081
01:17:17,887 --> 01:17:19,561
他们财务部出了点问题
They have a problem in their accounts department.

1082
01:17:19,586 --> 01:17:20,716
他们叫你马上过去
They need you up there straightaway.

1083
01:17:20,741 --> 01:17:23,104
是吗 我先把买的东西放好
Is that all? I'll just put the shopping away.

1084
01:17:23,129 --> 01:17:24,194
别管了
No, no, leave it.

1085
01:17:24,219 --> 01:17:25,577
那小伙子说 马上去
Straightaway, the young fella said.

1086
01:17:25,602 --> 01:17:27,267
妈妈 他说什么不重要
It doesn't matter what he said, Mother.

1087
01:17:27,292 --> 01:17:29,538
我又不是雇员 我这是在帮忙
I'm not an employee. I'd be doing them a favour.

1088
01:17:29,563 --> 01:17:31,810
我来管这些东西
Please, let me do the shopping.

1089
01:17:40,357 --> 01:17:42,711
现在是我们的旺季
The problem is that it's our busy season,

1090
01:17:42,736 --> 01:17:45,849
上周工人和司机都加了班
so all the mill workers and drivers did overtime last week.

1091
01:17:46,228 --> 01:17:48,947
他们都填了加班凭证
Well, they filled out the overtime slips,

1092
01:17:48,972 --> 01:17:49,892
但这里没人
but there's been nobody here

1093
01:17:49,893 --> 01:17:52,382
处理这些凭证 也没人处理工资单
to work it all out and to add to the wage slips,

1094
01:17:52,407 --> 01:17:54,514
有员工都开始抱怨了
and some of the men have started to complain,

1095
01:17:54,539 --> 01:17:55,915
我也不能怪他们
and I can't blame them.

1096
01:17:56,111 --> 01:17:58,612
你也看见了 现在一团糟
As you can see, it's all a terrible mess.

1097
01:18:01,785 --> 01:18:03,721
给我几个小时
Well, if you leave me for a couple of hours,

1098
01:18:03,746 --> 01:18:06,424
我就能弄出套系统 之后来接班的人
I can work out a system so that whoever comes in after me

1099
01:18:06,449 --> 01:18:07,723
也不会出问题
won't have any trouble.

1100
01:18:18,100 --> 01:18:19,094
你好 艾丽斯
Hello, Eilis.

1101
01:18:19,250 --> 01:18:20,138
玛利亚一直在和我说
Maria has been telling

1102
01:18:20,163 --> 01:18:22,101
你的工作做得很好
me you've done the most marvellous job here.

1103
01:18:22,380 --> 01:18:23,225
谢谢夸奖
Thank you.

1104
01:18:23,434 --> 01:18:24,331
我们应该预料到的
We should have known you would,

1105
01:18:24,356 --> 01:18:26,212
你毕竟是罗斯的妹妹
of course. You're Rose's sister, after all.

1106
01:18:26,403 --> 01:18:28,281
听说你有财务簿记的证书
I'm told you have a certificate in book-keeping.

1107
01:18:28,365 --> 01:18:30,164
是美国的簿记证书吗
Is it American book-keeping?

1108
01:18:30,238 --> 01:18:31,967
证书是在美国拿的
I got the certificate in America,

1109
01:18:31,968 --> 01:18:33,995
两套体系很相似
but the two systems are very similar.

1110
01:18:34,478 --> 01:18:37,219
旺季的时候 我们很需要人来
Well, we'll certainly need someone to deal with wages and so on

1111
01:18:37,244 --> 01:18:38,583
处理工资之类的事
during the busy season.

1112
01:18:38,851 --> 01:18:41,839
我希望你继续在我们这儿兼职
So I'd like you to continue on a part-time basis.

1113
01:18:41,864 --> 01:18:43,807
你先做着 然后我们再说
Let's see how that goes and then we'll speak again.

1114
01:18:44,330 --> 01:18:46,476
我马上就要回美国了
I'll be going back to the United States soon.

1115
01:18:46,501 --> 01:18:47,343
像我说的那样
As I say,

1116
01:18:47,368 --> 01:18:49,913
不管怎样 在做最后决定之前
let's you and I speak again before we make any firm decisions

1117
01:18:49,938 --> 01:18:51,237
我们俩谈一次
one way or the other.

1118
01:18:53,338 --> 01:18:56,400
好的 布朗先生 谢谢你
Yes, Mr Brown. Of course. Thank you.

1119
01:18:56,685 --> 01:18:59,598
要是你去找玛利亚 她会付给你今天的工钱
Now, if you go and see Maria, she'll have your money for today.

1120
01:20:02,534 --> 01:20:03,921
我都想不起来了
I'd forgotten.

1121
01:20:04,519 --> 01:20:05,557
什么
What?

1122
01:20:06,831 --> 01:20:07,903
这个
This.

1123
01:20:10,189 --> 01:20:12,156
布鲁克林也有沙滩呀
You have beaches in Brooklyn.

1124
01:20:12,882 --> 01:20:15,304
是啊 但那里很挤
Yes, but they're just very crowded.

1125
01:20:16,171 --> 01:20:19,032
晚点这里可能就有不少人了
There'll probably be quite a few walkers along here later.

1126
01:20:20,129 --> 01:20:21,140
是啊
Yes.

1127
01:20:21,938 --> 01:20:23,706
但还是不一样
It's still not the same.

1128
01:20:25,255 --> 01:20:26,782
我想也是
I'm sure it's not.

1129
01:20:28,719 --> 01:20:31,433
我们对世界其他地区一无所知
We don't really know anything of the rest of the world.

1130
01:20:32,837 --> 01:20:35,116
对你来说 我们肯定特别无知吧
We must seem very backward to you now.

1131
01:20:35,534 --> 01:20:36,868
当然不是了
Of course not.

1132
01:20:37,037 --> 01:20:40,393
你看起来既沉着 又有教养 还很有魅力
You seem calm and civilised and charming.

1133
01:20:46,809 --> 01:20:48,296
快来
Come on!

1134
01:20:55,960 --> 01:20:57,279
我母亲想要你知道
My mother wanted you to know

1135
01:20:57,304 --> 01:21:00,641
高尔夫俱乐部 要以罗斯的名字设立一个奖项
that the golf club is inaugurating a prize in Rose's name.

1136
01:21:03,422 --> 01:21:04,767
一个为得分最高的
A special trophy for the

1137
01:21:04,768 --> 01:21:07,315
俱乐部新人女士准备的特殊奖项
best score by a lady newcomer at the club.

1138
01:21:08,810 --> 01:21:11,740
我母亲说她一直对新人很友善
She was always very nice to the newcomers, my mother says.

1139
01:21:14,904 --> 01:21:16,182
希望你开心
I hope you're pleased.

1140
01:21:19,522 --> 01:21:20,583
是啊
Yes.

1141
01:21:21,961 --> 01:21:23,166
当然开心了
Of course.

1142
01:21:25,495 --> 01:21:31,032
所以每年都会有人赢得罗斯·莱西奖吗
So every year someone will win the Rose Lacey Trophy?

1143
01:21:31,997 --> 01:21:33,476
对啊 每年都会有
Yeah, every year,

1144
01:21:34,194 --> 01:21:36,052
只要高尔夫俱乐部还在
as long as there's a golf club.

1145
01:21:40,453 --> 01:21:44,543
我想她会很乐意 邀请你前来
And I think she'd like you to come along

1146
01:21:44,568 --> 01:21:46,524
给首位获胜者颁奖
and present it to the first winner.

1147
01:21:50,358 --> 01:21:51,470
而且 顺便说一句
Yeah, and my mother would like to

1148
01:21:51,495 --> 01:21:53,045
我母亲也很乐意见你一面的
meet you too, by the way.

1149
01:21:55,097 --> 01:21:58,006
我该安排个时间 邀请你过来喝茶
I'm supposed to arrange a time when you can come around for tea.

1150
01:21:59,453 --> 01:22:01,661
谢谢 我很乐意过去
Thank you. I'd like that.

1151
01:22:07,225 --> 01:22:09,585
真希望在我离开这里之前 就能这样
I wish it had been like this before I went.

1152
01:22:10,648 --> 01:22:12,183
在罗斯去世前
Before Rose died.

1153
01:22:13,511 --> 01:22:14,647
哪样
Like what?

1154
01:22:15,946 --> 01:22:18,094
之前我在这一无所有
There was nothing here for me before

1155
01:22:18,360 --> 01:22:20,069
而现在我有了份工作 而且...
and now I have a job and...

1156
01:22:20,984 --> 01:22:22,098
这里好吗
Here?

1157
01:22:37,523 --> 01:22:38,698
这是你从美国学来的招吗
Is that an American trick?

1158
01:22:38,884 --> 01:22:40,852
对啊 很棒吧 对吗
Yes. It's a good one, isn't it?

1159
01:22:43,042 --> 01:22:43,979
不过 我们以前从没想到过
It's depressing, though,

1160
01:22:43,980 --> 01:22:46,205
还能这样 真令人沮丧 对吗
that we don't think of things like that, isn't it?

1161
01:22:46,353 --> 01:22:49,000
我是说 他们这样做多久了
I mean, how long have they known about it?

1162
01:22:49,315 --> 01:22:50,618
可能一百年了吧
A hundred years, probably.

1163
01:22:51,028 --> 01:22:52,142
我想他们一百年前
I don't think they had

1164
01:22:52,143 --> 01:22:54,249
不会有这样子的泳衣吧
bathing suits like that a hundred years ago.

1165
01:22:55,627 --> 01:22:57,422
我们现在都没有
We still don't have them now.

1166
01:23:00,916 --> 01:23:01,971
好了 来吧
Well, come on.

1167
01:23:10,087 --> 01:23:12,315
你周六想去看道奇队的比赛吗
You wanna go see the Dodgers on Saturday?

1168
01:23:12,549 --> 01:23:14,066
- 当然了 - 那好
- Sure. - OK.

1169
01:23:14,246 --> 01:23:16,636
- 那你为我做件事吧 - 什么
- Will you do something for me? - What?

1170
01:23:16,916 --> 01:23:18,421
如果你笑了
If you laugh or you say

1171
01:23:18,446 --> 01:23:20,772
或者告诉家里别人这件事
anything about this to anybody in the family,

1172
01:23:20,797 --> 01:23:23,030
你周六 甚至这个季度 都别想去看
you don't get to go see the Dodgers on Saturday

1173
01:23:23,055 --> 01:23:24,493
道奇队的比赛了
or any other day of the season.

1174
01:23:24,721 --> 01:23:25,870
而且你会被打一顿
Also you get a beating.

1175
01:23:26,122 --> 01:23:28,414
那我还是不知道为好了
Maybe it's just better if I don't get involved.

1176
01:23:28,667 --> 01:23:30,333
我真的很需要你的帮助 弗兰基
I really need your help, Frankie.

1177
01:23:30,679 --> 01:23:33,024
你知道 你是家里最有文化的了吧
You know you're the best writer and reader in the family?

1178
01:23:33,049 --> 01:23:35,117
- 知道 - 我想写信给艾丽斯
- Yeah. - I'm trying to write to Eilis.

1179
01:23:35,142 --> 01:23:38,338
我想让信显得... 我不知道
And I want it to be... I don't know.

1180
01:23:38,517 --> 01:23:41,159
你之前都写过五次了
You've wrote before already about five times.

1181
01:23:41,212 --> 01:23:43,638
是啊 但写得不好 弗兰基 而且...
Yeah, but they're no good, Frankie, and...

1182
01:23:46,323 --> 01:23:48,378
她只回了我一次
She's only written back once.

1183
01:23:48,876 --> 01:23:51,037
她之前从来没读过我写的东西
She's never read my writing before.

1184
01:23:51,095 --> 01:23:53,241
我担心 我会让她厌烦
I'm worried I'm putting her off me.

1185
01:23:53,709 --> 01:23:55,807
听着 我才八岁
Listen, I'm eight years old.

1186
01:23:55,972 --> 01:23:57,630
我对接吻都一无所知
I don't know anything about kissing.

1187
01:23:57,655 --> 01:24:00,077
你不需要知道接吻啊
You don't need to know anything about kissing.

1188
01:24:00,426 --> 01:24:03,592
你只要知道拼写 还有...
You need to know about spelling and... and...

1189
01:24:03,617 --> 01:24:06,422
- 语法 - 对 你看看好吗
- Grammar. - Yeah. Will you look?

1190
01:24:15,391 --> 01:24:16,987
"亲爱的艾丽斯
"Dear Eilis.

1191
01:24:17,380 --> 01:24:20,216
希望你在爱尔兰过得好
I hope that you are doing well in Ireland.

1192
01:24:20,454 --> 01:24:23,344
希望你的母亲没那么悲伤了
I hope that your mother's feeling less sad.

1193
01:24:24,453 --> 01:24:27,587
距离你朋友结婚 然后你回来的日子
It will not be long before your friend gets married

1194
01:24:27,706 --> 01:24:29,684
已经不远了
and you can come home.

1195
01:24:32,536 --> 01:24:35,898
这周 好像全世界的地下室都淹水了一样
This week, it's like the whole world's basements are flooding.

1196
01:24:36,057 --> 01:24:37,692
我修了三家
I've fixed three.

1197
01:24:39,049 --> 01:24:42,029
我一直在努力工作 在存钱
I've been working hard. I've been saving money.

1198
01:24:43,155 --> 01:24:45,616
大家一直都在问我关于你的事"
Everybody asks me about you all the time."

1199
01:24:45,701 --> 01:24:47,451
我想你少写了一个"E"
You missed out an "E," I think.

1200
01:24:47,536 --> 01:24:49,808
是"大家"
It's "Everybody."

1201
01:24:51,777 --> 01:24:54,594
"总之 这就是我最近的事情了
"Anyway, I think that is all my news.

1202
01:24:54,684 --> 01:24:58,194
我父母和兄弟们向你问好
Mom and Dad and all my brothers, they all say hello.

1203
01:24:59,214 --> 01:25:02,383
我一天里大部分时间都在想你
I think about you most minutes of most days.

1204
01:25:03,911 --> 01:25:06,220
甚至在我去看道奇队比赛时
Even when I go see the Dodgers,

1205
01:25:06,346 --> 01:25:08,889
我都无法将注意力集中在比赛上
I do not concentrate on the games.

1206
01:25:10,434 --> 01:25:12,727
爱你的 托尼"
With love, your Tony."

1207
01:26:11,113 --> 01:26:12,620
没抹发油啊
No hair oil.

1208
01:26:13,347 --> 01:26:15,664
也没穿西装 穿了运动夹克
And that's not a blazer. It's a sports jacket.

1209
01:26:15,791 --> 01:26:17,422
你是乔装出来的吗 吉姆·法雷尔
Have you come out in disguise, Jim Farrell?

1210
01:26:17,447 --> 01:26:18,987
你是想捉弄我吗
Are you trying to trick me?

1211
01:26:21,070 --> 01:26:22,963
不 我只是理解了
No. I knew what you meant

1212
01:26:23,290 --> 01:26:25,013
你之前说我们没什么变化
when you said we were all the same.

1213
01:26:25,854 --> 01:26:28,612
你可能觉得 我的生活挺轻松的吧
It made me think that my life must seem very easy to you.

1214
01:26:28,773 --> 01:26:30,262
我经营着我父亲的酒吧
I run my father's bar.

1215
01:26:30,529 --> 01:26:32,584
又要住进我父母的房子里
I'm going to live in my parents' house.

1216
01:26:33,470 --> 01:26:36,310
我知道 表面看起来是这样的 但是...
I know what that must look like from the outside, but...

1217
01:26:37,952 --> 01:26:39,385
感觉却不一样
It doesn't feel like that.

1218
01:26:40,932 --> 01:26:42,441
感觉什么样呢
What does it feel like?

1219
01:26:46,236 --> 01:26:47,875
我从来没去过别的地方
And I've never been anywhere.

1220
01:26:47,900 --> 01:26:50,032
连英格兰都没去过
I've never even been to England

1221
01:26:50,321 --> 01:26:51,546
但我很想出去看看
but I'd like to see London

1222
01:26:51,571 --> 01:26:54,757
伦敦 巴黎 罗马 还有纽约
and Paris and Rome. New York.

1223
01:26:55,463 --> 01:26:58,833
从没有出过爱尔兰就死去 想想都无法接受
It frightens me, the idea of dying without ever leaving Ireland.

1224
01:26:59,000 --> 01:27:01,293
当然还有些别的事
And there are other things too.

1225
01:27:02,894 --> 01:27:05,582
很抱歉 我本来有很多事想问你
I'm so sorry, I wanted to ask you a thousand things

1226
01:27:05,607 --> 01:27:07,341
结果一直都是我在说
and all I've done is talked.

1227
01:27:07,647 --> 01:27:08,801
我很喜欢听
I'm glad.

1228
01:27:09,467 --> 01:27:11,561
- 真的吗 - 是啊
- Really? - Yes.

1229
01:27:14,059 --> 01:27:16,559
你能别抽了 跟我们坐下来聊聊吧
Will you finish that wretched pipe and sit with us?

1230
01:27:16,831 --> 01:27:18,607
我在这也能很清楚地听到你们说话
I can hear perfectly well from where I am.

1231
01:27:18,632 --> 01:27:20,509
我们在这不是让你当猴子来看的
We're not here to provide you with entertainment.

1232
01:27:20,534 --> 01:27:21,647
别担心
Oh, don't you worry.

1233
01:27:21,731 --> 01:27:23,315
我很多年前就知道这回事了
I found that out many years ago.

1234
01:27:23,623 --> 01:27:24,942
别理他 艾丽斯
Just ignore him, Eilis.

1235
01:27:25,193 --> 01:27:27,248
吉姆像我 不像他
It's as well Jim takes after me, not him.

1236
01:27:27,416 --> 01:27:28,368
声音大点
Speak up.

1237
01:27:28,975 --> 01:27:30,751
你们期待搬家吗
Are you looking forward to your move?

1238
01:27:30,939 --> 01:27:32,122
我们会想念恩尼斯科西的
We'll miss Enniscorthy,

1239
01:27:32,123 --> 01:27:33,784
但哥伦布恩也很不错 还很安静
but it's lovely and quiet in Glenbrien.

1240
01:27:33,966 --> 01:27:36,287
妈妈一直在担心留我一个人住在这
Mother's worried about leaving me here on me own.

1241
01:27:36,542 --> 01:27:38,101
她觉得我会把这地方毁了的
She thinks I'll destroy the place.

1242
01:27:38,126 --> 01:27:39,957
我只是担心你永远都孤单一人
Well, I'm hoping you won't be on your own forever.

1243
01:27:40,132 --> 01:27:41,375
他肯定不会的
I'm sure he won't.

1244
01:27:42,832 --> 01:27:44,137
我是说...
I mean...

1245
01:27:46,963 --> 01:27:48,418
天哪 天气难得这么好啊
God, aren't we blessed with this weather?

1246
01:27:48,849 --> 01:27:49,928
天气是很不错
It's lovely.

1247
01:27:51,357 --> 01:27:53,566
纽约的夏天很热吧
The summers in New York are hot, eh?

1248
01:27:54,100 --> 01:27:55,556
是啊 很热
They can be, yes.

1249
01:27:55,682 --> 01:27:58,191
有时候还会非常潮湿
It can get quite humid sometimes.

1250
01:28:05,775 --> 01:28:07,277
"亲爱的托尼
"Dear Tony.

1251
01:28:08,139 --> 01:28:10,138
谢谢你的来信
Thank you for your letters.

1252
01:28:10,969 --> 01:28:12,705
我想要你知道..."
I want you to know that..."

1253
01:28:16,536 --> 01:28:18,746
我不知道想要你知道什么
I don't know what I want you to know.

1254
01:28:31,930 --> 01:28:33,886
我不想坐在后面
I don't want to be sitting right at the back.

1255
01:28:33,911 --> 01:28:36,162
我们会确保你坐在最好的位置上的
We'll make sure you get the best seats in the house.

1256
01:28:36,590 --> 01:28:37,815
但跟南希和乔治坐在一起
But it wouldn't feel right

1257
01:28:37,816 --> 01:28:39,687
感觉也不太对
sitting up there with Nancy and George.

1258
01:28:40,349 --> 01:28:42,770
那就给你安排在第二好的座位吧
We'll find the second best seats in the house, then.

1259
01:28:45,466 --> 01:28:46,604
你要我先走一步
Would you like me to run ahead

1260
01:28:46,605 --> 01:28:48,692
去给你占几个座吗 莱西夫人
and save you a couple of places, Mrs Lacey?

1261
01:28:48,777 --> 01:28:51,126
你介意吗 吉姆 那太好了
Would you mind, Jim? That'd be grand.

1262
01:28:54,616 --> 01:28:57,324
- 真是个绅士啊 是吗 - 是啊
- Such a gentleman, isn't he? - He is.

1263
01:28:58,620 --> 01:29:00,978
我们在正确的时间遇见了他
Came along at just the right time for us.

1264
01:29:03,566 --> 01:29:05,543
我现在邀请你 南希
I invite you now, Nancy,

1265
01:29:05,710 --> 01:29:08,587
在上帝和教堂前宣布
to declare before God and his Church

1266
01:29:08,823 --> 01:29:12,171
你愿意成为乔治的妻子
your consent to become George's wife.

1267
01:29:14,091 --> 01:29:19,139
我将对你忠诚 不论顺境或逆境
I promise to be true to you in good times and in bad,

1268
01:29:19,389 --> 01:29:21,457
不论疾病或健康
in sickness and in health.

1269
01:29:21,947 --> 01:29:26,766
我会在我有生之年爱护你 尊重你
I will love you and honour you all the days of my life.

1270
01:29:28,151 --> 01:29:29,581
戒指
The rings.

1271
01:29:34,999 --> 01:29:37,242
主啊 保佑这对戒指
Lord, bless these rings.

1272
01:29:37,690 --> 01:29:40,077
给予戴上它的人
Grant that those who wear them

1273
01:29:40,392 --> 01:29:43,318
永远忠诚于对方
may always be faithful to each other.

1274
01:29:43,814 --> 01:29:45,332
愿他们在您的意志下
May they do your will

1275
01:29:45,534 --> 01:29:48,804
和平相处 互相关爱
and live in peace with you in mutual love.

1276
01:29:49,274 --> 01:29:53,007
我们要求如此 我主基督 阿门
We ask this through Christ our Lord, amen.

1277
01:29:53,628 --> 01:29:54,842
阿门
Amen.

1278
01:30:03,518 --> 01:30:06,496
你母亲告诉我 你在恩尼斯科西
Your mother tells me things are working out very well

1279
01:30:06,521 --> 01:30:08,822
一切都很顺利 艾丽斯
for you in Enniscorthy, Eilis.

1280
01:30:09,633 --> 01:30:11,233
这真是个隆重的仪式
It was a lovely service.

1281
01:30:11,485 --> 01:30:15,029
法雷尔夫妇要搬去哥伦布恩了
And Mr and Mrs Farrell are moving out to Glenbrien,

1282
01:30:15,221 --> 01:30:18,112
- 所以吉姆就... - 是的 我知道
- so Jim'll... - Yes, I know.

1283
01:30:18,610 --> 01:30:21,269
吉姆和我答应我母亲 要带她回车上的
Jim and I promised my mother we'd take her back to the car.

1284
01:30:21,294 --> 01:30:25,975
看你怎么说的 "吉姆和我 吉姆和我"
Mmm! Do you hear that? "Jim and I. Jim and I."

1285
01:30:26,000 --> 01:30:28,042
听起来你俩的好事也不远了
It won't be long now by the sound of it

1286
01:30:28,168 --> 01:30:31,085
你母亲一定会很开心的
and your mother will have a wonderful day out.

1287
01:30:32,043 --> 01:30:33,140
先失陪了
Will you excuse me?

1288
01:30:33,633 --> 01:30:35,007
他们在这呢
There they are.

1289
01:30:35,658 --> 01:30:37,787
- 你好 伯恩夫人 还好吗 - 杰克
- Hello, Mrs Byrne. How are you? - Jack.

1290
01:30:43,693 --> 01:30:44,915
我们能谈谈吗
Can we talk?

1291
01:30:47,046 --> 01:30:48,174
谈什么
What about?

1292
01:30:50,523 --> 01:30:51,832
未来
The future.

1293
01:30:52,994 --> 01:30:56,164
我不能让你什么都不说就回美国了
I can't let you just go back to America without saying anything.

1294
01:30:58,114 --> 01:31:00,341
这样我余生都会后悔的
I'd regret it for the rest of my life.

1295
01:31:02,535 --> 01:31:03,702
所以
So...

1296
01:31:04,969 --> 01:31:06,580
我不想要你走
I don't want you to go.

1297
01:31:07,582 --> 01:31:10,763
我想要你留在这 跟我在一起
I want you to stay here with me.

1298
01:31:13,498 --> 01:31:16,632
我知道这意味着 另一个问题
And I know that means asking you another question

1299
01:31:18,218 --> 01:31:20,277
但我不想连珠炮似地质问你
but I don't want to bombard you.

1300
01:31:22,162 --> 01:31:24,328
所以我晚一点再问你吧
So I'll save that one for later.

1301
01:31:29,938 --> 01:31:31,271
谢谢
Thank you.

1302
01:31:34,943 --> 01:31:36,443
我很感激
I'm grateful.

1303
01:31:37,774 --> 01:31:39,374
也很受宠若惊
And I'm flattered.

1304
01:31:41,783 --> 01:31:43,784
- 就这些吗 - 不
- That's all? - No.

1305
01:31:45,245 --> 01:31:47,246
不 当然不是
No, of course not.

1306
01:31:53,188 --> 01:31:54,559
我只是...
I just...

1307
01:31:57,173 --> 01:32:00,008
我想象中 我会过上另一种完全不同的生活
I'd imagined a different life for myself.

1308
01:32:00,923 --> 01:32:02,469
我理解
I understand.

1309
01:32:03,750 --> 01:32:06,140
但你在这生活 也能跟想象中一样好
But your life here could be just as good.

1310
01:32:07,362 --> 01:32:09,268
甚至可能更好
Better even maybe.

1311
01:32:50,850 --> 01:32:51,852
玛丽
Mary.

1312
01:32:52,645 --> 01:32:55,260
- 我正准备去接你 - 接我干什么
- I was just coming to fetch you. - To fetch me?

1313
01:32:55,320 --> 01:32:57,662
我已经很久不为凯丽小姐那工作了 玛丽
I haven't worked for Miss Kelly for a long time, Mary.

1314
01:32:57,687 --> 01:32:58,979
拜托来一趟吧 艾丽斯
Please come, Eilis.

1315
01:32:59,152 --> 01:33:00,834
她说找不到你 我就别回去了
She told me not to come back without you.

1316
01:33:01,049 --> 01:33:02,576
你知道她的脾气
You know what she's like.

1317
01:33:13,675 --> 01:33:15,081
我跟艾丽斯上楼的时候
You look after things for five

1318
01:33:15,106 --> 01:33:17,407
你替我照看五分钟的店 拜托了 玛丽
minutes while I'm upstairs with Eilis, please, Mary.

1319
01:33:17,576 --> 01:33:19,163
这个时候店里没有什么客人
There are no customers in there at the moment,

1320
01:33:19,188 --> 01:33:21,548
所以你应该不会搞得一团糟
so I don't think you can make too much of a mess of things.

1321
01:33:43,684 --> 01:33:46,194
最近怎么样啊
So, how have you been getting on?

1322
01:33:47,741 --> 01:33:49,076
非常好 谢谢 凯丽小姐
Very well, thanks, Miss Kelly.

1323
01:33:49,379 --> 01:33:51,703
我听说你在戴维斯那边的
I heard that you're working over in Davis's,

1324
01:33:51,788 --> 01:33:53,789
财务部工作
in the accounts department.

1325
01:33:54,024 --> 01:33:55,123
是的
That's right.

1326
01:33:55,318 --> 01:33:56,552
我也听到了很多
And there's lots of talk

1327
01:33:56,553 --> 01:33:58,669
关于你和吉姆·法雷尔的传言
about you and young Jim Farrell.

1328
01:33:58,753 --> 01:34:02,459
你知道的 大家就喜欢说些流言蜚语的
Oh, well, you know what people are like. They love to talk.

1329
01:34:02,484 --> 01:34:03,480
是啊
Yes.

1330
01:34:05,253 --> 01:34:07,719
你还记得布雷迪夫人吗
Do you remember Mrs Brady?

1331
01:34:09,821 --> 01:34:10,850
她经常在周日早上
She usually comes into

1332
01:34:10,851 --> 01:34:13,576
来店里买熏肉薄片
the shop on Sunday morning for her rashers.

1333
01:34:15,728 --> 01:34:16,810
不记得了吗
No?

1334
01:34:17,889 --> 01:34:20,399
那你现在过得很忙啊
Well, you have a very busy life now,

1335
01:34:20,590 --> 01:34:22,276
事情一件接一件的
what with one thing and another.

1336
01:34:23,570 --> 01:34:28,929
总之 布雷迪夫人有个侄女 住在布鲁克林
Anyway, Mrs Brady has a niece living in Brooklyn.

1337
01:34:32,412 --> 01:34:35,122
世界真小啊 是吗
The world is a small place, isn't it?

1338
01:34:35,877 --> 01:34:38,913
她几周前收到了一封侄女的来信
She had a letter from her a couple of weeks back.

1339
01:34:41,128 --> 01:34:42,519
上面写了什么
And what did it say?

1340
01:34:42,964 --> 01:34:46,728
只说了她去市政厅参加
Oh, only that she'd been to a wedding

1341
01:34:46,753 --> 01:34:47,968
一场婚礼
city hall

1342
01:34:48,573 --> 01:34:49,692
她丈夫无意中
and her husband bumped into

1343
01:34:49,693 --> 01:34:52,548
碰到一个来自恩尼斯科西的女孩
a girl from Enniscorthy

1344
01:34:52,773 --> 01:34:54,937
也在那登记结婚
who was getting married there.

1345
01:34:57,879 --> 01:34:59,938
我不太明白你想说什么 凯丽小姐
I'm not sure what you're telling me, Miss Kelly.

1346
01:35:00,023 --> 01:35:01,548
他没有碰见我
He didn't bump into me.

1347
01:35:01,717 --> 01:35:04,985
你可骗不了我 莱西小姐
Oh, you can't fool me, Miss Lacey.

1348
01:35:06,399 --> 01:35:10,880
虽然我都不确定 你的名字有没有换
Although I'm not sure that that's your name any longer, is it?

1349
01:35:11,423 --> 01:35:13,160
他不太记得了
He couldn't remember.

1350
01:35:14,306 --> 01:35:16,444
好像是意大利的姓吧
Something Italian, he thought.

1351
01:35:23,557 --> 01:35:24,838
我都忘了
I'd forgotten.

1352
01:35:24,923 --> 01:35:28,091
你都忘了 这简直...
You'd forgotten? What a thing...

1353
01:35:28,176 --> 01:35:30,677
我都忘了这个镇是什么样的了
I'd forgotten what this town is like.

1354
01:35:35,257 --> 01:35:37,643
凯丽小姐 你这么说有什么目的吗
What were you planning to do, Miss Kelly?

1355
01:35:39,103 --> 01:35:41,065
让我离吉姆远点吗
Keep me away from Jim?

1356
01:35:42,482 --> 01:35:45,025
还是想阻止我回美国
Stop me from going back to America?

1357
01:35:47,528 --> 01:35:49,613
或许连你自己都不知道
Perhaps you didn't even know.

1358
01:35:56,788 --> 01:36:00,457
我的名字是艾丽斯·费欧雷洛
My name is Eilis Fiorello.

1359
01:36:33,408 --> 01:36:35,826
- 现在就给你接过去 - 谢谢
- Putting you through now. - Thank you.

1360
01:36:36,167 --> 01:36:37,327
能帮你点什么吗
How can I help?

1361
01:36:37,633 --> 01:36:39,246
你好 我想预定一张
Hello. I'd like to make a reservation

1362
01:36:39,330 --> 01:36:42,499
从科夫去纽约的船票 越快越好
for the next available sailing from Cobh to New York.

1363
01:36:43,002 --> 01:36:45,836
我觉得人们婚礼后 反而花的钱更多了
I think people spend even more money after a wedding.

1364
01:36:46,034 --> 01:36:48,421
南希的母亲应该去遍了镇上所有的商店吧
Nancy's mother must have been in every shop in the town.

1365
01:36:48,446 --> 01:36:50,247
她都在布鲁姆店买好点火器了
She was buying firelighters in Broom's.

1366
01:36:50,421 --> 01:36:52,009
八月就买好了点火器
Firelighters in August.

1367
01:36:52,469 --> 01:36:54,594
她在那见到了斯泰普尔顿夫人 但还没来得及
But she'd seen Mrs Stapleton in there and she hadn't had a chance

1368
01:36:54,679 --> 01:36:57,347
跟她把婚礼的细节过一遍
to go through the whole day in detail with her...

1369
01:36:59,403 --> 01:37:00,726
艾丽斯 怎么了
Eilis, what's the matter?

1370
01:37:01,209 --> 01:37:02,674
你跟吉姆间出什么事了吗
Has something happened with Jim?

1371
01:37:03,991 --> 01:37:06,359
妈妈 对不起
Mammy, I'm sorry.

1372
01:37:07,499 --> 01:37:08,942
真的对不起
I'm so sorry.

1373
01:37:10,375 --> 01:37:11,943
我已经结婚了
I'm married.

1374
01:37:12,780 --> 01:37:15,625
我回家前就在布鲁克林结婚了
I got married in Brooklyn before I came home.

1375
01:37:15,650 --> 01:37:17,701
我应该告诉你的
And I should have told you.

1376
01:37:17,785 --> 01:37:20,579
我应该一回来就告诉你的
I should have told you as soon as I got back.

1377
01:37:25,378 --> 01:37:27,252
我想跟他在一起
I want to be with him.

1378
01:37:29,186 --> 01:37:31,050
我想跟我的丈夫在一起
I want to be with my husband.

1379
01:37:33,929 --> 01:37:35,260
当然了
Of course.

1380
01:37:38,382 --> 01:37:39,489
他人好吗
Is he nice?

1381
01:37:41,559 --> 01:37:42,642
很好
Yes.

1382
01:37:43,083 --> 01:37:45,169
你嫁的人一定很好
He'd have to be nice if you married him.

1383
01:37:48,158 --> 01:37:49,790
你要回去吗
So you're going back?

1384
01:37:51,319 --> 01:37:54,769
对 明天走
Yes. Tomorrow.

1385
01:37:58,299 --> 01:38:00,206
你要赶早班车吗
Are you on the early train?

1386
01:38:05,552 --> 01:38:07,015
我要去睡觉了
I'm going to bed.

1387
01:38:07,752 --> 01:38:11,088
妈妈 现在连八点都不到 别这样
Mammy, it's not even 8:00. You don't have to.

1388
01:38:11,172 --> 01:38:12,644
我很累了
I'm very tired.

1389
01:38:14,141 --> 01:38:16,624
我想现在就说再见
And I'd like to say goodbye now.

1390
01:38:18,875 --> 01:38:20,597
就说这一次
And only once.

1391
01:38:54,382 --> 01:38:56,605
你以后可以在信里写写他的事
Perhaps you'll write and tell me about him.

1392
01:38:57,174 --> 01:38:58,135
我会的
I will.

1393
01:38:59,649 --> 01:39:01,221
晚安 艾丽斯
Good night, Eilis.

1394
01:41:17,650 --> 01:41:19,634
你是要去美国生活吗
So are you away to live in America?

1395
01:41:21,169 --> 01:41:23,655
- 不 - 只是去看看吗
- No. - Just visiting?

1396
01:41:24,824 --> 01:41:26,862
不 我已经住在那了
No, I live there already.

1397
01:41:27,326 --> 01:41:29,861
真的吗 那里是什么样的
Really? What's it like?

1398
01:41:31,175 --> 01:41:33,076
那是一个很大的地方
It's a big place.

1399
01:41:35,232 --> 01:41:37,335
我要住在纽约的布鲁克林
I'm gonna live in Brooklyn, New York.

1400
01:41:38,208 --> 01:41:39,599
你知道那吗
Do you know it?

1401
01:41:41,439 --> 01:41:42,549
知道
Yes.

1402
01:41:44,148 --> 01:41:47,085
人们说那里有很多爱尔兰人
People say that there are so many Irish people there,

1403
01:41:47,873 --> 01:41:49,314
就像家一样
it's like home.

1404
01:41:52,691 --> 01:41:53,962
是真的吗
Is that right?

1405
01:41:58,824 --> 01:41:59,899
是的
Yes.

1406
01:42:00,870 --> 01:42:02,527
就像家一样
It's just like home.

1407
01:42:15,502 --> 01:42:16,979
你什么都别吃
You're not to eat.

1408
01:42:17,933 --> 01:42:19,749
但我要在那待很多年啊
But I might be there years.

1409
01:42:20,183 --> 01:42:21,970
不是 你到那之后随便吃
No, you can eat when you get there.

1410
01:42:21,995 --> 01:42:23,267
但别在船上吃东西
Don't eat on the boat.

1411
01:42:23,468 --> 01:42:25,984
这样你就不会晕船了 答应我好吗
It'll stop you getting so sick. Do you promise me?

1412
01:42:26,827 --> 01:42:27,677
我答应
I promise.

1413
01:42:27,762 --> 01:42:30,411
一会你就直接去你的房间
And in a moment I want you to go straight down to your cabin

1414
01:42:30,436 --> 01:42:32,406
从你这边把厕所门锁上
and lock the bathroom door on your side.

1415
01:42:32,875 --> 01:42:35,669
等隔壁开始锤门 你就跟他们协商
When next door starts hammering, you can negotiate.

1416
01:42:37,583 --> 01:42:40,273
等你到了移民局检查站 睁大眼睛
When you get to immigration, keep your eyes wide open.

1417
01:42:40,608 --> 01:42:42,359
一定要让自己看起来目标明确
Look as if you know where you're going.

1418
01:42:42,620 --> 01:42:44,653
一定要像美国人一样思考
You have to think like an American.

1419
01:42:47,091 --> 01:42:50,168
你会特别的想家 想得要死
You'll feel so homesick that you'll want to die

1420
01:42:50,642 --> 01:42:53,811
但除了忍耐以外 没有别的办法
and there's nothing you can do about it apart from endure it.

1421
01:42:55,498 --> 01:42:58,375
但你会做到的 这一切不会击垮你
But you will, and it won't kill you.

1422
01:43:13,057 --> 01:43:16,052
终有一天 太阳会升起
And one day the sun will come out.

1423
01:43:16,517 --> 01:43:18,311
但你可能都注意不到
You might not even notice straightaway,

1424
01:43:18,537 --> 01:43:20,371
因为它是那么的微弱
it'll be that faint.

1425
01:43:20,815 --> 01:43:21,852
之后你会开始
And then you'll catch

1426
01:43:21,877 --> 01:43:25,137
在意一些与过去无关的
yourself thinking about something or someone

1427
01:43:25,162 --> 01:43:27,679
人和事
who has no connection with the past,

1428
01:43:29,338 --> 01:43:31,563
在意一个只属于你的人
someone who's only yours,

1429
01:43:32,814 --> 01:43:34,522
那时你就会明白
and you'll realise...

1430
01:43:37,012 --> 01:43:39,345
此心安处是吾乡
that this is where your life is.


